*   WRITERM1=0;                     /* SET RECORD NUMBER FOR SEARCH     00429000
*                                      TO ZERO                       */ 00430000
         MVI   WRITERM1,X'00'                                      0205 00431000
*   RETCODE=NOTFULL;                /* INDICATE DATA SET NOT FULL    */ 00432000
         SLR   RETCODE,RETCODE                                     0206 00433000
*   END CCHHUPDT;                   /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00434000
         B     @EL00004                                            0207 00435000
*WRITEREC:                                                         0208 00436000
*                                                                  0208 00437000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00438000
*   /*                                                               */ 00439000
*   /* SUBROUTINE TO WRITE A RECORD TO SYS1.LOGREC                   */ 00440000
*   /*                                                               */ 00441000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00442000
*                                                                  0208 00443000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE,NOSAVEAREA);                                 0208 00444000
*                                                                  0208 00445000
WRITEREC STM   @14,@01,12(@13)                                     0208 00446000
         STM   @03,@12,32(@13)                                     0208 00447000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00448000
*   /*                                                               */ 00449000
*   /* SET UP COUNT FIELD OF RECORD                                  */ 00450000
*   /*                                                               */ 00451000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00452000
*                                                                  0209 00453000
*   CNTCCHH=WRITCCHH;               /* SET CCHH OF RECORD TO BE    0209 00454000
*                                      WRITTEN                       */ 00455000
         MVC   CNTCCHH(4),WRITCCHH                                 0209 00456000
*   CNTR=WRITERM1+1;                /* SET RECORD NUMBER OF RECORD TO   00457000
*                                      BE WRITTEN                    */ 00458000
         IC    @07,WRITERM1                                        0210 00459000
         LA    @07,1(,@07)                                         0210 00460000
         STC   @07,CNTR                                            0210 00461000
*   CNTDL=RECLNH;                   /* SET LENGTH OF RECORD TO BE  0211 00462000
*                                      WRITTEN                       */ 00463000
*                                                                  0211 00464000
         LH    @07,RECLNH                                          0211 00465000
         N     @07,@CF02443                                        0211 00466000
         STH   @07,CNTDL                                           0211 00467000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00468000
*   /*                                                               */ 00469000
*   /* ATTEMPT I/O AND CHECK RESULTS                                 */ 00470000
*   /*                                                               */ 00471000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00472000
*                                                                  0212 00473000
*   RWCKDCHN='1'B;                  /* INSURE DATA CHAINING ON IN  0212 00474000
*                                      WCKD CCW                      */ 00475000
         OI    RWCKDCHN,B'10000000'                                0212 00476000
*   R1=ADDR(RCCWS);                 /* POINT TO CCW'S TO WRITE RECORD*/ 00477000
         LA    R1,RCCWS                                            0213 00478000
*   BACKPTR=R13;                    /* CHAIN SAVE AREA TO CALLER'S   */ 00479000
         ST    R13,BACKPTR                                         0214 00480000
*   R13=ADDR(REGSAVE);              /* ESTABLISH NEW SAVE AREA PTR   */ 00481000
         LA    R13,REGSAVE                                         0215 00482000
*   CALL IGFPTRIO;                  /* ATTEMPT I/O TO WRITE RECORD   */ 00483000
         BAL   @14,IGFPTRIO                                        0216 00484000
*   R13=BACKPTR;                    /* RESTORE CALLER'S SAVE AREA PTR*/ 00485000
         L     R13,BACKPTR                                         0217 00486000
*   IF RETCODE¬=IOGOOD THEN         /* Q. I/O SUCCESSFUL             */ 00487000
         LTR   RETCODE,RETCODE                                     0218 00488000
         BNZ   @RT00218                                            0218 00489000
*     RETURN;                       /* NO, RETURN WITH CODE PASSED BY   00490000
*                                      IGFPTRIO                      */ 00491000
*   WRITERM1=WRITERM1+1;            /* UPDATE SEEK ADDR TO RECORD  0220 00492000
*                                      JUST WRITTEN                  */ 00493000
         IC    @07,WRITERM1                                        0220 00494000
         LA    @07,1(,@07)                                         0220 00495000
         STC   @07,WRITERM1                                        0220 00496000
*   HDRLAST=WRITESK;                /* UPDATE LOGREC HEADER WITH ADDR   00497000
*                                      OF RECORD JUST WRITTEN        */ 00498000
         MVC   HDRLAST(7),WRITESK                                  0221 00499000
*   HDRREMBT=REMBYTES;              /* UPDATE HEADER WITH BYTES    0222 00500000
*                                      REMAINING ON CURRENT TRACK    */ 00501000
         STH   REMBYTES,HDRREMBT                                   0222 00502000
*   UPDATSW='1'B;                   /* INDICATE HEADER HAS BEEN    0223 00503000
*                                      UPDATED                       */ 00504000
         OI    UPDATSW,B'10000000'                                 0223 00505000
*   END WRITEREC;                   /* RETURN TO CALLER WITH 'IOGOOD'   00506000
*                                      RETURN CODE                   */ 00507000
@EL00005 DS    0H                                                  0224 00508000
@EF00005 DS    0H                                                  0224 00509000
@ER00005 LM    @14,@01,12(@13)                                     0224 00510000
         LM    @03,@12,32(@13)                                     0224 00511000
         BR    @14                                                 0224 00512000
*WRITEHDR:                                                         0225 00513000
*                                                                  0225 00514000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00515000
*   /*                                                               */ 00516000
*   /* SUBROUTINE TO WRITE SYS1.LOGREC HEADER RECORD                 */ 00517000
*   /*                                                               */ 00518000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00519000
*                                                                  0225 00520000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE,NOSAVEAREA);                                 0225 00521000
WRITEHDR STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0225 00522000
*   HREADCMD=WRITDATA;              /* CHANGE COMMAND CODE IN 'READ     00523000
*                                      DATA' CCW TO 'WRITE DATA'     */ 00524000
         MVI   HREADCMD,X'05'                                      0226 00525000
*   R1=ADDR(HCCWS);                 /* POINT TO CCWS TO WRITE LOGREC    00526000
*                                      HEADER                        */ 00527000

*   BACKPTR=R13;                    /* CHAIN SAVE AREA TO CALLER'S   */ 00529000
         ST    R13,BACKPTR                                         0228 00530000
*   R13=ADDR(REGSAVE);              /* ESTABLISH NEW SAVE AREA PTR   */ 00531000

*   CALL IGFPTRIO;                  /* ATTEMPT I/O TO WRITE HEADER   */ 00533000
         BAL   @14,IGFPTRIO                                        0230 00534000
*   R13=BACKPTR;                    /* RESTORE CALLER'S SAVE AREA PTR*/ 00535000
         L     R13,BACKPTR                                         0231 00536000
*   END WRITEHDR;                   /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00537000
@EL00006 DS    0H                                                  0232 00538000
@EF00006 DS    0H                                                  0232 00539000
@ER00006 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0232 00540000
         BR    @14                                                 0232 00541000
*WRITEOF:                                                          0233 00542000
*                                                                  0233 00543000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00544000
*   /*                                                               */ 00545000
*   /* SUBROUTINE TO WRITE EOF RECORD ON SYS1.LOGREC                 */ 00546000
*   /*                                                               */ 00547000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00548000
*                                                                  0233 00549000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE,NOSAVEAREA);                                 0233 00550000
WRITEOF  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0233 00551000
*   BACKPTR=R13;                    /* CHAIN SAVE AREA TO CALLER'S   */ 00552000
         ST    R13,BACKPTR                                         0234 00553000
*   R13=ADDR(REGSAVE);              /* ESTABLISH NEW SAVE AREA PTR   */ 00554000
         LA    R13,REGSAVE                                         0235 00555000
*   CNTDL=0;                        /* ZERO DATA LENGTH PORTION OF 0236 00556000
*                                      COUNT FIELD TO SIGNIFY EOF  0236 00557000
*                                      RECORD                        */ 00558000
         SLR   @07,@07                                             0236 00559000
         STH   @07,CNTDL                                           0236 00560000
*   IF HDRLSTCH=HDRHILIM THEN       /* Q. LAST RECORD PUT ON LAST  0237 00561000
*                                      TRACK                         */ 00562000
         CLC   HDRLSTCH(4),HDRHILIM                                0237 00563000
         BNE   @RF00237                                            0237 00564000
*     DO;                           /* YES, EOF WILL BE WRITTEN AS 0238 00565000
*                                      NEXT RECORD ON LAST TRACK     */ 00566000
*       WRITERM1=HDRLSTR;           /* SET SEARCH ID TO RECORD NUMBER   00567000
*                                      OF LAST RECORD WRITTEN        */ 00568000
         IC    @15,HDRLSTR                                         0239 00569000
         STC   @15,WRITERM1                                        0239 00570000
*       CNTR='FF'X;                 /* SET RECORD NUMBER IN COUNT  0240 00571000
*                                      FIELD TO MAXIMUM VALUE        */ 00572000
         MVI   CNTR,X'FF'                                          0240 00573000
*       RECLNH=0;                   /* SET UP PARM FOR SEEIFFIT    0241 00574000
*                                      (LENGTH OF DATA PORTION OF  0241 00575000
*                                      RECORD TO BE WRITTEN)         */ 00576000
         STH   @07,RECLNH                                          0241 00577000
*       CALL SEEIFFIT;              /* SEE IF EOF RECORD WILL FIT    */ 00578000
         BAL   @14,SEEIFFIT                                        0242 00579000
*       IF RETCODE¬=GOODFIT THEN    /* Q. ENOUGH SPACE FOR EOF RECORD*/ 00580000
         LTR   RETCODE,RETCODE                                     0243 00581000
         BZ    @RF00243                                            0243 00582000
*         DO;                       /* NO, FORGET ABOUT IT           */ 00583000
*           R13=BACKPTR;            /* RESTORE CALLER'S SAVE AREA PTR*/ 00584000
         L     R13,BACKPTR                                         0245 00585000
*           RETURN;                 /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00586000
@EL00007 DS    0H                                                  0246 00587000
@EF00007 DS    0H                                                  0246 00588000
@ER00007 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0246 00589000
         BR    @14                                                 0246 00590000
*         END;                                                     0247 00591000
*     END;                                                         0248 00592000
*   ELSE                            /* EOF WILL BE WRITTEN AS FIRST     00593000
*                                      RECORD OF LAST TRACK          */ 00594000
*     DO;                                                          0249 00595000
         B     @RC00237                                            0249 00596000
@RF00237 DS    0H                                                  0250 00597000
*       CNTCCHH=HDRHILIM;           /* SET CCHH IN COUNT FIELD TO  0250 00598000
*                                      CCHH OF LAST TRACK            */ 00599000
         MVC   CNTCCHH(4),HDRHILIM                                 0250 00600000
*       CNTR=1;                     /* SET RECORD NUMBER IN COUNT  0251 00601000
*                                      FIELD TO 1                    */ 00602000
         MVI   CNTR,X'01'                                          0251 00603000
*       WRITCCHH=HDRHILIM;          /* SET CCHH IN SEEK FIELD TO CCHH   00604000
*                                      OF LAST TRACK                 */ 00605000
         MVC   WRITCCHH(4),HDRHILIM                                0252 00606000
*       WRITERM1=0;                 /* SET RECORD NUMBER FOR SEARCH     00607000
*                                      TO 0                          */ 00608000
         MVI   WRITERM1,X'00'                                      0253 00609000
*     END;                                                         0254 00610000
*   RWCKDCHN='0'B;                  /* REMOVE DATA CHAINING FROM WCKD   00611000
*                                      CCW SINCE NO DATA IS TO BE  0255 00612000
*                                      WRITTEN                       */ 00613000
@RC00237 NI    RWCKDCHN,B'01111111'                                0255 00614000
*   R1=ADDR(RCCWS);                 /* POINT TO CCW'S TO WRITE EOF   */ 00615000
         LA    R1,RCCWS                                            0256 00616000
*   CALL IGFPTRIO;                  /* ATTEMPT I/O TO WRITE EOF      */ 00617000
         BAL   @14,IGFPTRIO                                        0257 00618000
*   R13=BACKPTR;                    /* RESTORE CALLER'S SAVE AREA PTR*/ 00619000
         L     R13,BACKPTR                                         0258 00620000
*   END WRITEOF;                    /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00621000
         B     @EL00007                                            0259 00622000
*IGFPTRIO:                                                         0260 00623000
*                                                                  0260 00624000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00625000
*   /*                                                               */ 00626000
*   /* SUBROUTINE TO DO I/O TO SYS1.LOGREC                           */ 00627000
*   /*                                                               */ 00628000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00629000
*                                                                  0260 00630000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE,NOSAVEAREA);                                 0260 00631000
*                                                                  0260 00632000
IGFPTRIO STM   @14,@01,12(@13)                                     0260 00633000
         STM   @03,@12,32(@13)                                     0260 00634000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00635000
*   /*                                                               */ 00636000
*   /* SAVE CURRENT I/O STATUS AND PERFORM INITIAL HOUSEKEEPING      */ 00637000

*   /*****************************************************************/ 00639000
*                                                                  0261 00640000
*   IONEWSAV=FLCINPSW;              /* SAVE I/O NEW PSW              */ 00641000

*   IOOLDSAV=FLCIOPSW;              /* SAVE I/O OLD PSW              */ 00643000

*   CSWSAVE=FLCCSW;                 /* SAVE CSW                      */ 00649000

*   GEN REFS(CHMSKSAV,CHMSKNEW) SETS(CHMSKSAV);                    0266 00651000

         LCTL  2,2,CHMSKNEW           INSURE ALL CHANNELS MASKED ON     00653000
*   IOSWTCHS=0;                     /* INITIALIZE SWITCHES USED BY 0267 00654000
*                                      THIS SUBROUTINE               */ 00655000

         MVC   FLCINPSW(8),MYIONPSW                                0268 00660000
*   LOGCUA=UCBCHAN;                 /* GET CHANNEL AND UNIT ADDR OF     00661000
*                                      LOGREC DEVICE                 */ 00662000
         L     @15,CVTPTR                                          0269 00663000
         L     @15,DCBPTR-1(,@15)                                  0269 00664000

         L     @15,UCBPTR+32(,@15)                                 0269 00666000
         LH    LOGCUA,UCBCHAN(,@15)                                0269 00667000
         N     LOGCUA,@CF02443                                     0269 00668000
*CAWSETUP:                                                         0270 00669000
*   FLCCAW=R1;                      /* PUT INPUT CCW ADDR IN CAW     */ 00670000
*                                                                  0270 00671000
CAWSETUP ST    R1,FLCCAW                                           0270 00672000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00673000
*   /*                                                               */ 00674000
*   /* INSURE THAT THE PATH TO THE LOGREC DEVICE IS CLEAR AND ISSUE  */ 00675000
*   /* SIO                                                           */ 00676000
*   /*                                                               */ 00677000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00678000
*                                                                  0271 00679000
*CLRPATH:                                                          0271 00680000
*   TCH(LOGCUA);                    /* TEST AVAILABILITY OF CHANNEL  */ 00681000
CLRPATH  TCH   0(LOGCUA)                                           0271 00682000
*   BC(1,NOGOOD);                   /* CC=3, CHANNEL NOT OPERATIONAL    00683000
*                                      - QUIT                        */ 00684000
         BC    1,NOGOOD                                            0272 00685000
*   BC(6,INTPEND);                  /* CC=1 OR 2, INTERRUPT PENDING -   00686000
*                                      WAIT FOR IT                   */ 00687000
         BC    6,INTPEND                                           0273 00688000
*/*                                    CC=0, CHANNEL AVAILABLE       */ 00689000
*                                                                  0274 00690000
*   HIO(LOGCUA);                    /* SEE IF DEVICE CAN BE ACCESSED */ 00691000
         HIO   0(LOGCUA)                                           0274 00692000

*   DO SPINCTR=SPINVAL BY-1 TO 1;   /* HIO MAY CAUSE BUSY CONDITION     00696000

*   BC(11,STARTIO);                 /* CC¬=1, SIO CAN BE ATTEMPTED   */ 00708000

*/*                                    CC=1,CSW STORED               */ 00710000
*                                                                  0280 00711000
*   IF CSWICC='1'B|CSWCCC='1'B THEN /* Q. INTERFACE OR CHANNEL     0280 00712000
*                                      CONTROL CHECK                 */ 00713000

         BZ    @RF00280                                            0280 00715000
*     DO;                           /* YES, FORGET SIO FOR NOW AND 0281 00716000
*                                      SEE IF ANOTHER ATTEMPT SHOULD    00717000

*CHKRETRY:                                                         0282 00719000

*   BC(1,NOGOOD);                   /* CC=3, HARDWARE NOT OPERATIONAL   00737000
*                                      - QUIT                        */ 00738000

*   BC(4,CHKCSW);                   /* CC=1, CSW STORED - CHECK IT 0291 00740000

         BC    4,CHKCSW                                            0291 00742000
*   BC(2,SIOBUSY);                  /* CC=2, CHANNEL BUSY - WAIT FOR    00743000

         BC    2,SIOBUSY                                           0292 00745000
*/*                                    CC=0, I/O INITIATED           */ 00746000
*                                                                  0293 00747000

*   /*                                                               */ 00764000

*   IF CSWLOGP='1'B                 /* CHECK FOR CHANNEL LOGOUT    0299 00770000

*       |CSWICC='1'B                /* CHECK FOR INTERFACE CONTROL 0299 00772000

         BNZ   @RT00302                                            0302 00792000
*       GOTO CLRPATH;               /* IF ANY OF THE ABOVE THEN    0303 00793000
*                                      REPEAT SEQUENCE TO CLEAR THE     00794000

         B     INTPEND                                             0304 00799000

*                                      INTERRUPTION                  */ 00802000
*       |CSWIL='1'B                 /* CHECK FOR INCORRECT LENGTH    */ 00803000
*       |CSWPTNCK='1'B              /* CHECK FOR PROTECTION CHECK    */ 00804000
*       |CSWPGMCK='1'B              /* CHECK FOR PROGRAM CHECK       */ 00805000
*       |CSWCHNCK='1'B THEN         /* CHECK FOR CHAINING CHECK      */ 00806000

         LA    @03,SENSECCW                                        0309 00817000
         ST    @03,FLCCAW                                          0309 00818000
*       SIO(LOGCUA);                /* ATTEMPT START I/O FOR SENSE   */ 00819000

*       BC(7,NOGOOD);               /* CC¬=0, QUIT                   */ 00821000

*       LPSW(WAITPSW);              /* WAIT FOR SENSE TO COMPLETE    */ 00825000
         LPSW  WAITPSW                                             0313 00826000
*     END;                                                         0314 00827000
*   ELSE                                                           0315 00828000
*     GOTO NOGOOD;                  /* IF CSW STORED AND NONE OF   0315 00829000
*                                      ABOVE TESTS ARE SATISFIED THEN   00830000
*                                      QUIT                          */ 00831000
*                                                                  0315 00832000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00833000
*   /*                                                               */ 00834000
*   /* INTERNAL I/O INTERRUPT HANDLER POINTED TO BY I/O NEW PSW      */ 00835000

./  ADD  SSI=71250504,NAME=IGFPWMSG
         TITLE 'IGFPWMSG - OPERATOR MESSAGE WRITER                     *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IGFPWMSG CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IGFPWMSG  77.125'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
         BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00011000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00013000
         L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0001 00014000
         GETMAIN  R,LV=(0)                                              00015000
         LR    @11,@01                                             0001 00016000
         USING @DATD,@11                                           0001 00017000
         ST    @13,@SA00001+4                                      0001 00018000
         LM    @00,@01,20(@13)                                     0001 00019000
         ST    @11,8(,@13)                                         0001 00020000
         LR    @13,@11                                             0001 00021000
*                                                                  0058 00022000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00023000
*   /*                                                               */ 00024000
*   /* SEARCH MESSAGE BUFFER POOL FOR ACTIVE BUFFERS                 */ 00025000
*   /*                                                               */ 00026000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00027000
*                                                                  0058 00028000
*   DO MSGPTR=RVTMSGPT BY LENGTH(MSG) WHILE MSGPTR<RVTMSGPT+RVTMSGLN;   00029000
         L     @10,CVTPTR                                          0058 00030000
         L     @10,RVTPTR(,@10)                                    0058 00031000
         L     MSGPTR,RVTMSGPT(,@10)                               0058 00032000
         B     @DE00058                                            0058 00033000
@DL00058 DS    0H                                                  0059 00034000
*                                   /*                       @YM00999*/ 00035000
*     TS(MSGCTL);                   /* IS BUFFER BUSY                */ 00036000
         TS    MSGCTL(MSGPTR)                                      0059 00037000
*     BC(8,NEXT);                   /* NO. GET NEXT BUFFER           */ 00038000
*                                                                  0060 00039000
         BC    8,NEXT                                              0060 00040000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00041000
*     /*                                                             */ 00042000
*     /* ACTIVE BUFFER HAS BEEN FOUND. NOW IT MUST BE DETERMINED IF A*/ 00043000
*     /* VALID MESSAGE NUMBER IS CONTAINED IN THE MSGNUM FIELD. NOTE */ 00044000
*     /* THAT MSGNUM='00'X MEANS THAT THE BUFFER IS NOT COMPLETELY   */ 00045000
*     /* SET UP YET.                                                 */ 00046000
*     /*                                                             */ 00047000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00048000
*                                                                  0061 00049000
*     IF MSGNUM¬='00'X THEN         /* IS MESSAGE COMPLETELY SET UP     00050000
*                                                            @YM00999*/ 00051000
         CLI   MSGNUM(MSGPTR),X'00'                                0061 00052000
         BE    @RF00061                                            0061 00053000
*       DO;                         /* YES, PROCESS IT       @YM00999*/ 00054000
*                                                                  0062 00055000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00056000
*         /*                                                         */ 00057000
*         /* THE VARIABLES NECESSARY FOR THE PROCESSING OF EACH      */ 00058000
*         /* INDIVIDUAL MESSAGE MUST BE INITIALIZED AT THIS TIME.    */ 00059000
*         /*                                                         */ 00060000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00061000
*                                                                  0063 00062000
*         IF MSGNUM='58'X THEN      /* IS THIS THE ACR MESSAGE     0063 00063000
*                                                            @G55DP2M*/ 00064000
         CLI   MSGNUM(MSGPTR),X'58'                                0063 00065000
         BNE   @RF00063                                            0063 00066000
*           IF MSGTAB1='FF'X THEN   /* YES- IS THE MESSAGE TO BE   0064 00067000
*                                      PRINTED               @G55DP2M*/ 00068000
         CLI   MSGTAB1(MSGPTR),X'FF'                               0064 00069000
         BNE   @RF00064                                            0064 00070000
*             MSGTAB1='00'X;        /* YES- RESET INDICATOR  @G55DP2M*/ 00071000
         MVI   MSGTAB1(MSGPTR),X'00'                               0065 00072000
*           ELSE                                                   0066 00073000
*             GOTO OUT;             /* NO - GET OUT OF LOOP  @G55DP2M*/ 00074000
*         FOUNDRC=NOTFND;           /* INDICATE THAT MSGNUM NOT FOUND*/ 00075000
@RF00063 LA    FOUNDRC,4                                           0067 00076000
*         MSGPTIND=MSGNUM;          /* GET MESSAGE NUMBER FROM RVT 0068 00077000
*                                      BUFFER                        */ 00078000
         MVC   MSGPTIND(1),MSGNUM(MSGPTR)                          0068 00079000
*         INDEX=1;                  /* INITIALIZE THE STACK WITH   0069 00080000
*                                      POINTER TO TOP                */ 00081000
         LA    @10,1                                               0069 00082000
         LR    INDEX,@10                                           0069 00083000
*         TBLFCNT=1;                /* INITIALIZE TABLE FIELD      0070 00084000
*                                      COUNT(ALLOW FOR TWO ENTRIES)  */ 00085000
         LR    TBLFCNT,@10                                         0070 00086000
*         VARFCNT=0;                /* INITIALIZE VARIABLE FIELD   0071 00087000
*                                      COUNT(ALLOW FOR TWO HEX(X)  0071 00088000
*                                      REPLACES OR ONE CHAR.(C)    0071 00089000
*                                      REPLACE                       */ 00090000
         SLR   VARFCNT,VARFCNT                                     0071 00091000
*         OUTCOUNT=1;               /* INITIALIZE COUNT OF OUTPUT  0072 00092000
*                                      CHARACTERS TO 1               */ 00093000
         LR    OUTCOUNT,@10                                        0072 00094000
*         OUTBUFF=' ';              /* CLEAR ACTUAL WTO OUTPUT BUFFER*/ 00095000
         MVI   OUTBUFF+1,C' '                                      0073 00096000
         MVC   OUTBUFF+2(118),OUTBUFF+1                            0073 00097000
         MVI   OUTBUFF,C' '                                        0073 00098000
*/****************************************************************   */ 00099000
*/*                                                                  */ 00100000
*/*  SUBROUTINE FIND WILL BE USED TO LOCATE THE MESSAGE NUMBER       */ 00101000
*/*   IF THE MESSAGE NUMBER IS NOT IN THE TABLE,FIND WILL RE-        */ 00102000
*/*   TURN A VALUE IN THE FOUND RETURN CODE(FOUNDRC) OF              */ 00103000
*/*   FOUR. A VALUE OF 0(FND) INDICATES MESSAGE FRAGMENT FOUND       */ 00104000
*/*                                                                  */ 00105000
*/****************************************************************   */ 00106000
*                                                                  0074 00107000
*         CALL FIND;                /* FIND MESSAGE TO PROCESS       */ 00108000
         BAL   @14,FIND                                            0074 00109000
*         IF FOUNDRC=FND THEN       /* IS MESSAGE FOUND ?            */ 00110000
         LTR   FOUNDRC,FOUNDRC                                     0075 00111000
         BNZ   @RF00075                                            0075 00112000
*           DO;                     /* YES - GET READY FOR WTO     0076 00113000
*                                                            @YM00999*/ 00114000
*             DO WHILE INDEX>0;                                    0077 00115000
         B     @DE00077                                            0077 00116000
@DL00077 DS    0H                                                  0078 00117000
*               TEXTPTR=STAKPTR(INDEX);/* LAST TEXT ADDRESS          */ 00118000
         LR    @10,INDEX                                           0078 00119000
         SLA   @10,3                                               0078 00120000
         L     TEXTPTR,STAKPTR-8(@10)                              0078 00121000
*               DO TEXTCNT=STAKCNT(INDEX) BY-1 WHILE TEXTCNT>0;    0079 00122000
         L     TEXTCNT,STAKCNT-8(@10)                              0079 00123000
         B     @DE00079                                            0079 00124000
@DL00079 DS    0H                                                  0080 00125000
*                 OUTBUFF(OUTCOUNT)=INCHAR;/* MOVE ONE CHAR          */ 00126000
         LA    @10,OUTBUFF-1(OUTCOUNT)                             0080 00127000
         MVC   0(1,@10),INCHAR(TEXTPTR)                            0080 00128000
*                 IF INCHAR='%' THEN                               0081 00129000
         CLI   INCHAR(TEXTPTR),C'%'                                0081 00130000
         BNE   @RF00081                                            0081 00131000
*                   DO;                                            0082 00132000
*                     TEXTPTR=TEXTPTR+1;/* INCREMENT POSITION OF   0083 00133000
*                                      TEXTPTR                       */ 00134000
         AL    TEXTPTR,@CF00078                                    0083 00135000
*                     IF INCHAR='X'|INCHAR='D' THEN                0084 00136000
         CLI   INCHAR(TEXTPTR),C'X'                                0084 00137000
         BE    @RT00084                                            0084 00138000
         CLI   INCHAR(TEXTPTR),C'D'                                0084 00139000
         BNE   @RF00084                                            0084 00140000
@RT00084 DS    0H                                                  0085 00141000
*                       CALL CONVERT;/* CONVERT TO PRINTABLE CHAR    */ 00142000
         BAL   @14,CONVERT                                         0085 00143000
*                     ELSE                                         0086 00144000
*                       IF INCHAR='C' THEN                         0086 00145000
         B     @RC00084                                            0086 00146000
@RF00084 CLI   INCHAR(TEXTPTR),C'C'                                0086 00147000
         BNE   @RF00086                                            0086 00148000
*                         CALL CHARCONV;/* MOVE CHARACTERS           */ 00149000
         BAL   @14,CHARCONV                                        0087 00150000
*                       ELSE                                       0088 00151000
*                         IF INCHAR='T' THEN                       0088 00152000
         B     @RC00086                                            0088 00153000
@RF00086 CLI   INCHAR(TEXTPTR),C'T'                                0088 00154000
         BNE   @RF00088                                            0088 00155000
*                           CALL REPLACE;/* REPLACE WITH STRING      */ 00156000
         BAL   @14,REPLACE                                         0089 00157000
*                         ELSE                                     0090 00158000
*                           OUTCOUNT=OUTCOUNT+1;/* % NOT FOLLOWED BY    00159000
*                                      VALID CHAR                    */ 00160000
         B     @RC00088                                            0090 00161000
@RF00088 AL    OUTCOUNT,@CF00078                                   0090 00162000
*                   END;                                           0091 00163000
*                 ELSE                                             0092 00164000
*                   DO;                                            0092 00165000
         B     @RC00081                                            0092 00166000
@RF00081 DS    0H                                                  0093 00167000
*                     OUTCOUNT=OUTCOUNT+1;/* INCREMENT OUTPUT COUNTER*/ 00168000
         LA    @10,1                                               0093 00169000
         ALR   OUTCOUNT,@10                                        0093 00170000
*                     TEXTPTR=TEXTPTR+1;/* INCREMENT POINTER TO INPUT   00171000
*                                      TEXT                          */ 00172000
         ALR   TEXTPTR,@10                                         0094 00173000
*                   END;                                           0095 00174000
*               END;                /* THIS ENDS THE PROCESSING FOR A   00175000
*                                      MESSAGE FRAGMENT              */ 00176000
*                                                                  0096 00177000
@RC00081 BCTR  TEXTCNT,0                                           0096 00178000
@DE00079 LTR   TEXTCNT,TEXTCNT                                     0096 00179000
         BP    @DL00079                                            0096 00180000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00181000
*               /*                                                   */ 00182000
*               /* NOW UPDATE THE INDEX VALUE TO SEE IF FRAGMENTS    */ 00183000
*               /* HAVE BEEN STACKED                                 */ 00184000
*               /*                                                   */ 00185000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00186000
*                                                                  0097 00187000
*               INDEX=INDEX-1;      /* DECREMENT SKELETON POSITION 0097 00188000
*                                      POINTER                       */ 00189000
         BCTR  INDEX,0                                             0097 00190000
*             END;                                                 0098 00191000
*                                                                  0098 00192000
@DE00077 LTR   INDEX,INDEX                                         0098 00193000
         BP    @DL00077                                            0098 00194000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00195000
*             /*                                                     */ 00196000
*             /* A COMPLETE MESSAGE HAS BEEN SET UP AT THIS POINT NOW*/ 00197000
*             /* THE MESSAGE MUST BE WRITTEN TO THE OPERATOR AND     */ 00198000
*             /* FURTHUR SEARCH OF THE RVT MESSAGE BUFFER RESUMED    */ 00199000
*             /*                                                     */ 00200000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00201000
*                                                                  0099 00202000
*             CALL WTORTN;          /* ISSUE WTO                     */ 00203000
         BAL   @14,WTORTN                                          0099 00204000
*             IF MSGNUM='58'X THEN                                 0100 00205000
         CLI   MSGNUM(MSGPTR),X'58'                                0100 00206000
         BNE   @RF00100                                            0100 00207000
*               DO;                 /* THIS IS THE ACR MSG   @ZM45609*/ 00208000
*                 MSGVAR1=0;        /* RESET CPU ADDR IN MSG @ZM45609*/ 00209000
         SLR   @10,@10                                             0102 00210000
         STCM  @10,15,MSGVAR1(MSGPTR)                              0102 00211000
*                 GOTO OUT;         /* DONT RESET MSGNUM OR MSGCTL 0103 00212000
*                                                            @ZM45609*/ 00213000
         B     OUT                                                 0103 00214000
*               END;                /*                       @ZM45609*/ 00215000
*           END;                    /*                       @YM00999*/ 00216000
@RF00100 DS    0H                                                  0106 00217000
*         MSGNUM='00'X;             /* RESET MESSAGE NUMBER IN BUFFER   00218000
*                                                            @YM00999*/ 00219000
@RF00075 MVI   MSGNUM(MSGPTR),X'00'                                0106 00220000
*NEXT:                                                             0107 00221000
*         ;                                                        0107 00222000
NEXT     DS    0H                                                  0108 00223000
*         MSGCTL='00'X;             /* ZERO MESSAGE CONTROL FLAG FOR    00224000
*                                      FREE BUFFER                   */ 00225000
         MVI   MSGCTL(MSGPTR),X'00'                                0108 00226000
*       END;                                                       0109 00227000
*OUT:                                                              0110 00228000
*     ;                                                            0110 00229000
@RF00061 DS    0H                                                  0110 00230000
OUT      DS    0H                                                  0111 00231000
*   END;                                                           0111 00232000
*                                                                  0111 00233000
         AL    MSGPTR,@CF00032                                     0111 00234000
@DE00058 L     @10,CVTPTR                                          0111 00235000
         L     @10,RVTPTR(,@10)                                    0111 00236000
         L     @04,RVTMSGPT(,@10)                                  0111 00237000
         AL    @04,RVTMSGLN(,@10)                                  0111 00238000
         CR    MSGPTR,@04                                          0111 00239000
         BL    @DL00058                                            0111 00240000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00241000
*   /*                                                               */ 00242000
*   /* ENTRY AT THIS POINT INDICATES THAT ALL POSSIBLE MESSAG ES HAVE*/ 00243000
*   /* BEEN WRITTEN.                                                 */ 00244000
*   /*                                                               */ 00245000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00246000
*                                                                  0112 00247000
*   RETURN;                         /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00248000
*                                                                  0112 00249000
@EL00001 L     @13,4(,@13)                                         0112 00250000
@EF00001 L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0112 00251000
         LR    @01,@11                                             0112 00252000
         FREEMAIN R,LV=(0),A=(1)                                        00253000
@ER00001 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0112 00254000
         BR    @14                                                 0112 00255000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00256000
*   /*                                                               */ 00257000
*   /* FIND SUBROUTINE IS USED TO LOCATE A MESSAGE FRAGMENT IN THE   */ 00258000
*   /* MESSAGE SKELETON . A POINTER TO THE DESIRED FRAGMENT EXISTS AT*/ 00259000
*   /* FIELD MSGPTIND. THIS VALUE IS COMPARED AGAINST THE SKELKEY    */ 00260000
*   /* FIELD OF EACH TABLE ENTRY.                                    */ 00261000
*   /*                                                               */ 00262000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00263000
*                                                                  0113 00264000
*FIND:                                                             0113 00265000
*   PROC;                           /* PROCEDURE TO LOCATE MESSAGE 0113 00266000
*                                      FRAGMENT                      */ 00267000
FIND     STM   @14,@05,12(@13)                                     0113 00268000
         STM   @07,@12,48(@13)                                     0113 00269000
*   FOUNDRC=NOTFND;                 /* INITIALIZE BAD RETURN CODE    */ 00270000
         LA    FOUNDRC,4                                           0114 00271000
*   DO SKELNDX=1 TO SKELENT WHILE FOUNDRC¬=FND;/* GET READY TO SEARCH   00272000
*                                      SKELETON              @YM00999*/ 00273000
         LA    SKELNDX,1                                           0115 00274000
         B     @DE00115                                            0115 00275000
@DL00115 LTR   FOUNDRC,FOUNDRC                                     0115 00276000
         BZ    @DC00115                                            0115 00277000
*     IF SKELKEY(SKELNDX)=MSGPTIND  /* SEARCH SKELETON KEY           */ 00278000
*       THEN                                                       0116 00279000
         LR    @10,SKELNDX                                         0116 00280000
         MH    @10,@CH01056                                        0116 00281000
         LA    @07,SKELKEY-57(@10)                                 0116 00282000
         CLC   0(1,@07),MSGPTIND                                   0116 00283000
         BNE   @RF00116                                            0116 00284000
*       DO;                                                        0117 00285000
*         STAKPTR(INDEX)=ADDR(SKELTEXT(SKELNDX));/* FOUND            */ 00286000
         LR    @07,INDEX                                           0118 00287000
         SLA   @07,3                                               0118 00288000
         LA    @15,SKELTEXT-57(@10)                                0118 00289000
         ST    @15,STAKPTR-8(@07)                                  0118 00290000
*         STAKCNT(INDEX)=SKELLNG(SKELNDX);/* SAVE LENGTH             */ 00291000
         SLR   @15,@15                                             0119 00292000
         IC    @15,SKELLNG-57(@10)                                 0119 00293000
         ST    @15,STAKCNT-8(@07)                                  0119 00294000
*         FOUNDRC=FND;              /* INDICATE MSG. FRAGMENT FOUND  */ 00295000
         SLR   FOUNDRC,FOUNDRC                                     0120 00296000
*       END;                                                       0121 00297000
*     ELSE                                                         0122 00298000
*       ;                                                          0122 00299000
@RF00116 DS    0H                                                  0123 00300000
*   END;                                                           0123 00301000

*   PROC;                           /* PROCEDURE TO PROCESS 'T'    0126 00314000

*   /*                                                               */ 00326000

*   /* THE STAK,BUMP THE STAK INDEX AND SEE IF A VALID SUBSTUTION    */ 00329000
*   /* CHARACTER IS FOUND IN THE SKELETON.                           */ 00330000
*   /*                                                               */ 00331000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00332000
*                                                                  0128 00333000

*       /*                                                           */ 00366000

*       /*                                                           */ 00369000

*                                                                  0139 00371000

*           /*                                                       */ 00390000

*           /*                                                       */ 00392000

         BCTR  INDEX,0                                             0147 00403000
*         END;                                                     0148 00404000
*     END;                                                         0149 00405000

*     OUTCOUNT=OUTCOUNT+1;          /* ADJUST COUNT SO 'T' IS MOVED  */ 00407000

*   RETURN;                         /* RETURN TO MAINLINE            */ 00410000

*CHARCONV:                                                         0153 00420000
*   PROC;                           /* PROCEDURE TO HANDLE 'C' CHAR.    00421000

         STM   @09,@12,56(@13)                                     0153 00425000
*   VARFCNT=VARFCNT+4;              /* ADJUST VARFCNT TO GET CORRECT    00426000
*                                      INDEX                         */ 00427000

*   IF VARFCNT<5                                                   0155 00429000
*                                                                  0155 00430000

*   /*                                                               */ 00432000
*   /* IF VARFCNT IS LESS THAN FIVE THAN THIS IS A VALID CHARACTER   */ 00433000
*   /* SUBSTITUTION.THE INDICES WILL BE UPDATED AND THE 8 CHARACTERS */ 00434000
*   /* MOVED.IF THE VARFCNT(VARIABLE FIELD COUNT) IS 5 OR MORE THAN  */ 00435000
*   /* THE CHARACTER SUBSTUTION IS INVALID NAD THE 'C' MUST BE MOVED */ 00436000
*   /* LIKE ANY OTHER INPUT CHARACTER                                */ 00437000

*   /*****************************************************************/ 00439000
*                                                                  0155 00440000

*   ELSE                                                           0163 00463000

@EF00004 DS    0H                                                  0164 00470000

*CONVERT:                                                          0166 00477000
*   PROC;                           /* PROCEDURE TO HANDLE 'X' AND '    00478000
*                                      D' NUMERICAL MSG. SUBST.      */ 00479000

*                                      FIELD                         */ 00484000

*                                      VARIABLE                      */ 00519000

         ALR   @10,VARFCNT                                         0178 00521000

*       CVD(R1,UNPKOUT);            /* CONVERT TO DECIMAL            */ 00523000

*       UNPK(OUTPUT,UNPKOUT);       /* MAKE IT PRINTABLE             */ 00525000

*                                                                  0183 00533000

*   /*                                                               */ 00535000
*   /* CALCULATE THE NUMBER OF LEADING ZEROS TO BE SUPRESSED         */ 00536000
*   /*                                                               */ 00537000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00538000
*                                                                  0184 00539000
*   DO N=1 BY 1 TO LMAX WHILE OUTPUT(N)='0';                       0184 00540000

*   N=N-1;                          /* GET ACTUAL NUMBER OF LEADING     00551000

*                                                                  0186 00553000

*   /*                                                               */ 00556000

*   /*                                                               */ 00558000

./  ADD  SSI=71300387,NAME=IGFPXMFA
         TITLE 'IGFPXMFA - MALFUNCTION ALERT EXTERNAL SLIH             *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IGFPXMFA CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT BALR  @15,0                                               0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(15)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IGFPXMFA 77130 '                                  0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00010000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00011000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00012000
*                                                                  0063 00013000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00014000
*   /*                                                               */ 00015000
*   /* CHECK IF FAILING CPU IS ALIVE (ONLINE)                        */ 00016000
*   /*                                                               */ 00017000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00018000
*                                                                  0063 00019000
*   PSAPTR=0;                       /* GET ADDR OF EXECUTING CPU'S 0063 00020000
*                                      PSA                           */ 00021000
         SLR   PSAPTR,PSAPTR                                       0063 00022000
*   RFY                                                            0064 00023000
*    (CPUALMSK,                                                    0064 00024000
*     CPUADDR) RSTD;                                               0064 00025000
*   CPUALMSK=CPUALFLD;              /* GET MASK OF CPU'S ALIVE IN  0065 00026000
*                                      HIGH-ORDER TWO BYTES OF     0065 00027000
*                                      'CPUALMSK' REG                */ 00028000
         L     @07,CVTPTR(,PSAPTR)                                 0065 00029000
         L     @15,CVTCSD(,@07)                                    0065 00030000
         L     CPUALMSK,CPUALFLD(,@15)                             0065 00031000
*   CPUADDR=PSASPAD;                /* GET ADDR OF FAILING CPU       */ 00032000
         LH    @15,PSASPAD(,PSAPTR)                                0066 00033000
         LR    CPUADDR,@15                                         0066 00034000
*   PCCAPTR=PCCAT00P(PSASPAD+1);    /* GET ADDR OF FAILING CPU'S PCCA   00035000
*                                      IF ON STILL EXISTS (IF THE CPU   00036000
*                                      IS NOT ONLINE THIS FIELD MAY     00037000
*                                      BE ZERO)                      */ 00038000
         SLA   @15,2                                               0067 00039000
         L     @07,CVTPCCAT(,@07)                                  0067 00040000
         L     PCCAPTR,PCCAT00P(@15,@07)                           0067 00041000
*   PSAPTR=PCCAPSAV;                /* GET ADDR OF FAILING CPU'S PSA    00042000
*                                      (IF PCCA EXISTS FOR THAT CPU) */ 00043000
         L     PSAPTR,PCCAPSAV(,PCCAPTR)                           0068 00044000
*   GEN REFS(CPUALMSK,CPUADDR) SETS(CPUALMSK);                     0069 00045000
         SLL   CPUALMSK,0(CPUADDR)     SHIFT 'ALIVE' BIT ASSOCIATED     00046000
*                                         WITH FAILING CPU TO HIGH      00047000
*                                         ORDER POSITION                00048000
         LTR   CPUALMSK,CPUALMSK       Q. FAILING CPU ALIVE             00049000
         BL    CPUALIVE                YES, BRANCH                      00050000
*   IF PCCAPTR¬=0 THEN              /* Q. PCCA EXISTS FOR FAILING  0070 00051000
*                                      DEAD CPU                      */ 00052000
         LTR   PCCAPTR,PCCAPTR                                     0070 00053000
         BZ    @RF00070                                            0070 00054000
*     PCCACPUM='1'B;                /* MFA ALREADY RECEIVED@G47AN2O  */ 00055000
         OI    PCCACPUM(PCCAPTR),B'10000000'                       0071 00056000
*   GEN(BR    RETNREG)                                             0072 00057000
*   REFS(RETNREG) NOSETS;           /* RETURN TO EXTERNAL FLIH       */ 00058000
@RF00070 DS    0H                                                  0072 00059000
         BR    RETNREG                                                  00060000
         EJECT                                                          00061000
*                                                                  0073 00062000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00063000
*   /*                                                               */ 00064000
*   /* CHECK IF MALFUNCTION ALERT IS ALREADY BEING PROCESSED BY      */ 00065000
*   /* ANOTHER CPU                                                   */ 00066000
*   /*                                                               */ 00067000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00068000
*                                                                  0073 00069000
*CPUALIVE:                                                         0073 00070000
*   TS(PWAMFAFL);                   /* Q. MALFUNCTION ALERT ALREADY     00071000
*                                      BEING PROCESSED               */ 00072000
CPUALIVE L     @07,PWAPTR(,PCCAPTR)                                0073 00073000
         TS    PWAMFAFL(@07)                                       0073 00074000
*   GEN(BCR   4,RETNREG)                                           0074 00075000
*   REFS(RETNREG) NOSETS;           /* YES, RETURN TO EXTERNAL FLIH  */ 00076000
*                                                                  0074 00077000
         BCR   4,RETNREG                                                00078000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00079000
*   /*                                                               */ 00080000
*   /* CHECK IF SYSTEM TERMINATION IS IN PROGRESS                    */ 00081000
*   /*                                                               */ 00082000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00083000
*                                                                  0075 00084000
*   IF RWATERM¬=NOTTERM THEN        /* Q. SYSTEM TERMINATION IN    0075 00085000
*                                      PROGRESS                      */ 00086000
         L     @07,CVTPTR(,PSAPTR)                                 0075 00087000
         L     @07,RVTPTR(,@07)                                    0075 00088000
         L     @15,RWAPTR(,@07)                                    0075 00089000
         CLC   RWATERM(8,@15),NOTTERM                              0075 00090000
         BE    @RF00075                                            0075 00091000
*     CALL IGFPTSIG;                /* YES, EXIT TO IGFPTSIG (NOTE 0076 00092000
*                                      THAT REG 2 STILL CONTAINS THE    00093000
*                                      SAME VALUE AS AT ENTRY)       */ 00094000
         L     @15,RVTPTSIG(,@07)                                  0076 00095000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0076 00096000
         EJECT                                                          00097000
*                                                                  0077 00098000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00099000
*   /*                                                               */ 00100000
*   /* ISSUE SIGP SENSE TO VERIFY THAT FAILING CPU IS IN CHECK-STOP  */ 00101000
*   /* OR STOPPED STATE - THAT IS, CONDITION CODE 1 WITH CHECK-STOP  */ 00102000
*   /* OR STOPPED STATUS INDICATED. IF CONDITION CODE 3 IS RETURNED  */ 00103000
*   /* ON THE SIGP SENSE, NO FURTHER ATTEMPT IS MADE TO DETERMINE THE*/ 00104000
*   /* CPU STATUS OR STOP THE CPU. IF CONDITION CODE 0 OR 2 IS       */ 00105000
*   /* RECEIVED, A SIGP STOP IS ISSUED. THE ENTIRE SEQUENCE          */ 00106000
*   /* (BEGINNING WITH THE SIGP SENSE) IS RE-EXECUTED UP TO 100 TIMES*/ 00107000
*   /* UNTIL CHECK-STOP OR STOPPED STATUS IS INDICATED.      @G55BP2M*/ 00108000
*   /*                                                               */ 00109000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00110000
*                                                                  0077 00111000
*   LOOPCNTR=100;                   /* DO UP TO 100 TIMES    @G55BP2M*/ 00112000
@RF00075 LA    LOOPCNTR,100                                        0077 00113000
*   DO WHILE LOOPCNTR>0;            /*                       @G55BP2M*/ 00114000
         B     @DE00078                                            0078 00115000
@DL00078 DS    0H                                                  0079 00116000
*     WKREGB=0;                     /* CLEAR STATUS REG      @G55BP2M*/ 00117000
         SLR   WKREGB,WKREGB                                       0079 00118000
*     GENERATE CODE REFS(WKREGA,WKREGB,CPUADDR,EXITLOOP);          0080 00119000
*                                                        /* @G55BP2M*/  00120000
         SIGP  WKREGB,CPUADDR,SIGPSEN    ISSUE SIGP SENSE   @G55BP2M    00121000
         BC    1,EXITLOOP                CC=3, EXIT         @G55BP2M    00122000
         BC    2,STOPIT                  CC=2, ISSUE STOP   @G55BP2M    00123000
*                                        CC=0 OR 1          @G55BP2M    00124000
         N     WKREGB,SIGPSCKS           TEST FOR STOP OR   @G55BP2M    00125000
         LTR   WKREGB,WKREGB             CHECK-STOP STATE   @G55BP2M    00126000
         BNZ   EXITLOOP                  YES, EXIT LOOP     @G55BP2M    00127000
STOPIT   SIGP  WKREGB,CPUADDR,SIGPSTOP   ELSE SIGP STOP     @G55BP2M    00128000
*     LOOPCNTR=LOOPCNTR-1;          /* DECREMENT COUNTER     @G55BP2M*/ 00129000
         BCTR  LOOPCNTR,0                                          0081 00130000
*   END;                            /*                       @G55BP2M*/ 00131000
@DE00078 LTR   LOOPCNTR,LOOPCNTR                                   0082 00132000
         BP    @DL00078                                            0082 00133000
*   RFY                                                            0083 00134000
*    (CPUALMSK,                                                    0083 00135000
*     CPUADDR) UNRSTD;              /*                       @G55BP2M*/ 00136000
*                                                                  0083 00137000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00138000
*   /*                                                               */ 00139000
*   /* NOW ENSURE THAT IF CPU LEAVES STOPPED OR CHECK-STOPPED STATE  */ 00140000
*   /* IT WILL ENTER AN 'A27' WAIT STATE                     @G55BP2M*/ 00141000
*   /*                                                               */ 00142000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00143000
*                                                                  0084 00144000
*EXITLOOP:                                                         0084 00145000
*   FLCRNPSW=STOPPSW;               /* RESTART NEW PSW       @G55BP2M*/ 00146000
EXITLOOP MVC   FLCRNPSW(8,PSAPTR),STOPPSW                          0084 00147000
*   FLCENPSW=STOPPSW;               /* EXTERNAL NEW PSW      @G55BP2M*/ 00148000
         MVC   FLCENPSW(8,PSAPTR),STOPPSW                          0085 00149000
*   FLCSNPSW=STOPPSW;               /* SVC NEW PSW           @G55BP2M*/ 00150000
         MVC   FLCSNPSW(8,PSAPTR),STOPPSW                          0086 00151000
*   FLCPNPSW=STOPPSW;               /* PROGRAM CHECK NEW PSW @G55BP2M*/ 00152000
         MVC   FLCPNPSW(8,PSAPTR),STOPPSW                          0087 00153000
*   FLCMNPSW=STOPPSW;               /* MACHINE CHECK NEW PSW @G55BP2M*/ 00154000
         MVC   FLCMNPSW(8,PSAPTR),STOPPSW                          0088 00155000
*   FLCINPSW=STOPPSW;               /* I/O NEW PSW           @G55BP2M*/ 00156000
         MVC   FLCINPSW(8,PSAPTR),STOPPSW                          0089 00157000
*                                                                  0090 00158000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00159000
*   /*                                                               */ 00160000
*   /* PUT STATUS OF FAILING CPU IN LRB                      @Z30LQLM*/ 00161000
*   /*                                                               */ 00162000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00163000
*                                                                  0090 00164000
*   IF PSAMCHIC='00'X THEN          /* Q. LRB ALREADY SET UP BY MCH  */ 00165000
         CLI   PSAMCHIC(PSAPTR),X'00'                              0090 00166000
         BNE   @RF00090                                            0090 00167000
*     DO;                           /* NO, MUST CONSTRUCT LRB OURSELF*/ 00168000
*       TS(LRBMCLB);                /* SET LRB CLOBBER FLAGS         */ 00169000
         L     @05,LRBPTR(,PCCAPTR)                                0092 00170000
         TS    LRBMCLB(@05)                                        0092 00171000
*       LRBMMOSW=FLCMOPSW;          /* MOVE MACHINE CHECK OLD PSW TO    00172000
*                                      LRB                           */ 00173000
         MVC   LRBMMOSW(8,@05),FLCMOPSW(PSAPTR)                    0093 00174000
*       LRBMFLO(1:256)=FIXEDLOG(1:256);/* MOVE FIXED LOGOUT AREA TO     00175000
*                                      LRB                           */ 00176000
         MVC   LRBMFLO(256,@05),FIXEDLOG(PSAPTR)                   0094 00177000
*       LRBMFLO(257:LENGTH(LRBMFLO))=FIXEDLOG(257:LENGTH(LRBMFLO));     00178000
         MVC   LRBMFLO+256(24,@05),FIXEDLOG+256(PSAPTR)            0095 00179000
*       LRBMLNH=LENGTH(LRB)         /* LENGTH OF LRB = LENGTH OF   0096 00180000
*                                      HEADER                        */ 00181000

*   /*                                                               */ 00209000

*   /* PROCESSOR                                             @Z30LQLM*/ 00211000

*   /*****************************************************************/ 00213000
*                                                                  0104 00214000

./  ADD  SSI=32201345,NAME=IGFRINIT
         TITLE 'IGFRINIT - RMS MODEL DEPENDENT INITIALIZATION          *00001000
                       '                                                00002000
IGFRINIT CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IGFRINIT  73.222'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
         BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00011000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00013000
         ST    @13,@SA00001+4                                      0001 00014000
         LA    @14,@SA00001                                        0001 00015000
         ST    @14,8(,@13)                                         0001 00016000
         LR    @13,@14                                             0001 00017000
*                                                                       00018000
* REFS ARE GENERATED FOR NVT FIELDS THAT CONTAIN ADDRESSES OF           00019000
* NIP SERVICE ROUTINES, SO IEAPMNIP MACRO CALLS TO THESE ROUTINES       00020000
* WILL ASSEMBLE PROPERLY.                                               00021000
*                                                                  0076 00022000
*/**************************************************************     */ 00023000
*                                                                  0077 00024000
*   RPARM=ADDR(PARMS);                                             0077 00025000
         LA    RPARM,PARMS                                         0077 00026000
*   BLDLAST=ADDR(BLDLENT(8));       /* STORE LAST BLDL ENTRY ADDRESS */ 00027000
         LA    @14,BLDLENT+406                                     0078 00028000
         ST    @14,BLDLAST                                         0078 00029000
*   BLDLNXT=ADDR(BLDLENT(1));       /* STORE FIRST BLDL ENTRY ADDRESS*/ 00030000
         LA    @14,BLDLENT                                         0079 00031000
         ST    @14,BLDLNXT                                         0079 00032000
*   BLDLPTR=ADDR(BLDLLST);          /* LOAD ADDRESS OF BLDL LIST     */ 00033000
         LA    @14,BLDLLST                                         0080 00034000
         ST    @14,BLDLPTR                                         0080 00035000
*   RMSNIP='1'B;                    /* SET IGFRINIT IN PROGRESS IN 0081 00036000
*                                      IGFRMS                        */ 00037000
