         END   IGFTMC00,(C'PLS2115',0701,78073)                         04280000
./  ADD  SSI=33180432,NAME=IGF2503D
         TITLE 'IGF2503D, DDR - SWAP COMMAND PROCESSOR                 *00001000
                       '                                                00002000
IGF2503D CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IGF2503D  73.318'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  BALR  @08,0                                               0001 00010000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00011000
         USING @PSTART,@08                                         0001 00012000
         L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0001 00013000
         GETMAIN R,LV=(0)                                               00014000
         LR    @09,@01                                             0001 00015000
         USING @DATD,@09                                           0001 00016000
         ST    @13,@SA00001+4                                      0001 00017000
         LR    @13,@09                                             0001 00018000
*                                      INTERFACE TO IGFDV1           */ 00019000
*   SRTNADDR=RTNADDR;               /* SAVE RETURN ADDRESS - THIS IS    00020000
*                                      NECESSARY SINCE REGISTERS WERE   00021000
*                                      NOT AUTOMATICALLY SAVED BY PLS   00022000
*                                      BECAUSE NO SAVE AREA POINTER     00023000
*                                      IS PASSED TO THIS MODULE      */ 00024000
         LR    SRTNADDR,RTNADDR                                    0135 00025000
*   DDRPTR=ADDR(LDDRCOM);           /* POINT TO LOCAL DDRCOM         */ 00026000
         LA    DDRPTR,LDDRCOM                                      0136 00027000
*   LDDRCOM=LDDRCOM&&LDDRCOM;       /* CLEAR LOCAL DDRCOM            */ 00028000
         XC    LDDRCOM(100),LDDRCOM                                0137 00029000
*   SAVEXSA=XSAPTR;                 /* SAVE XSA ADDRESS              */ 00030000
         ST    XSAPTR,SAVEXSA                                      0138 00031000
*   DO;                             /* ?IGFDERR INIT                 */ 00032000
*                                                                  0139 00033000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00034000
*     /*                                                             */ 00035000
*     /* IGFDERR - INITIALIZE RECOVERY ENVIRONMENT                   */ 00036000
*     /*                                                             */ 00037000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00038000
*                                                                  0140 00039000
*     DERPLIST=DERPLIST&&DERPLIST;  /* CLEAR PARAMETER LIST          */ 00040000
         XC    DERPLIST(48),DERPLIST                               0140 00041000
*     DERFUNK=DERINIT;              /* INDICATE INIT FUNCTION        */ 00042000
         MVI   DERFUNK,X'01'                                       0141 00043000
*     DERREC=ADDR(DERRECPM);        /* POINT TO REC PARMS            */ 00044000
         LA    @12,DERRECPM                                        0142 00045000
         ST    @12,DERREC                                          0142 00046000
*     DERRETRY=ADDR(IGF2503R);      /* POINT TO RETRY ROUTINE        */ 00047000
         LA    @12,IGF2503R                                        0143 00048000
         ST    @12,DERRETRY                                        0143 00049000
*     GEN SETS(DERDATD)(MVC DERDATD,@SIZDATD);/* SET UP SPN, SIZE    */ 00050000
         MVC DERDATD,@SIZDATD                                           00051000
*     DERPFX=DERRMASK;              /* SET UP RUB MASK               */ 00052000
         MVC   DERPFX(2),@CB00750                                  0145 00053000
*     DERRCODE=CODEBASE;            /* SAVE CODEREG                  */ 00054000
         ST    CODEBASE,DERRCODE                                   0146 00055000
*     DERRDATA=DATABASE;            /* SAVE DATAREG                  */ 00056000
         ST    DATABASE,DERRDATA                                   0147 00057000
*     DERRDDR=DDRPTR;               /* SAVE DDRCOM POINTER           */ 00058000
         ST    DDRPTR,DERRDDR                                      0148 00059000
*     DERRSAVE=SAVEPTR;             /* SAVE REGISTER 13              */ 00060000
         ST    SAVEPTR,DERRSAVE                                    0149 00061000
*     CALL IGFDE0(DERPLIST);        /* ISSUE ESTAE                   */ 00062000
         LA    @12,DERPLIST                                        0150 00063000
         ST    @12,@AL00001                                        0150 00064000
         L     @15,@CV00080                                        0150 00065000
         LA    @01,@AL00001                                        0150 00066000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0150 00067000
*   END;                            /* ?IGFDERR INIT                 */ 00068000
*   DERLRC=INVALID;                 /* INDICATE PARAMETER ERROR      */ 00069000
*                                                                  0152 00070000
         MVI   DERLRC,X'04'                                        0152 00071000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00072000
*   /*                                                               */ 00073000
*   /* THERE MUST BE AN OPERAND ON THE SWAP COMMAND - IF SO, PROCESS */ 00074000
*   /* IT - IF NOT, THE SWAP COMMAND IS INVALID                      */ 00075000
*   /*                                                               */ 00076000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00077000
*                                                                  0153 00078000
*   IF XAL=0 THEN                   /* IS THERE AN OPERAND           */ 00079000
         ICM   @12,7,XAL(XSAPTR)                                   0153 00080000
         BNZ   @RF00153                                            0153 00081000
*     XAE=PARMMSNG;                 /* NO, INDICATE PARAMETER MISSING*/ 00082000
         MVI   XAE(XSAPTR),X'0B'                                   0154 00083000
*   ELSE                            /* YES, PROCESS COMMAND          */ 00084000
*     IF CTEXT(1:2)='ON' THEN       /* IS IT 'SWAP ON'               */ 00085000
         B     @RC00153                                            0155 00086000
@RF00153 SR    @12,@12                                             0155 00087000
         ICM   @12,7,XAL(XSAPTR)                                   0155 00088000
         CLC   CTEXT(2,@12),@CC01615                               0155 00089000
         BNE   @RF00155                                            0155 00090000
*       CALL IGFON;                 /* YES, ACTIVATE DDR             */ 00091000
         BAL   @14,IGFON                                           0156 00092000
*     ELSE                          /* NO, TRY FOR OTHER OPERANDS    */ 00093000
*       IF CTEXT(1:3)='OFF' THEN    /* IS IT 'SWAP OFF'              */ 00094000
         B     @RC00155                                            0157 00095000
@RF00155 SR    @12,@12                                             0157 00096000
         ICM   @12,7,XAL(XSAPTR)                                   0157 00097000
         CLC   CTEXT(3,@12),@CC01617                               0157 00098000
         BNE   @RF00157                                            0157 00099000
*         CALL IGFOFF;              /* YES, DEACTIVATE DDR           */ 00100000
         BAL   @14,IGFOFF                                          0158 00101000
*       ELSE                        /* NO, MUST BE 'SWAP XXX,YYY'    */ 00102000
*         CALL IGFSWAP;             /* VALIDATE SWAP REQUEST         */ 00103000
         B     @RC00157                                            0159 00104000
@RF00157 BAL   @14,IGFSWAP                                         0159 00105000
*IGF2503R:                          /* ESTAE RETRY ROUTINE ENTRY PT  */ 00106000
*   DO;                             /* ?IGFDERR CANCEL               */ 00107000
*                                                                  0160 00108000
@RC00157 DS    0H                                                  0160 00109000
@RC00155 DS    0H                                                  0160 00110000
@RC00153 DS    0H                                                  0160 00111000
IGF2503R DS    0H                                                  0161 00112000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00113000
*     /*                                                             */ 00114000
*     /* IGFDERR - CANCEL RECOVERY ENVIRONMENT                       */ 00115000
*     /*                                                             */ 00116000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00117000
*                                                                  0161 00118000
*     DERFUNK=DERCANC;              /* INDICATE CANCEL               */ 00119000
         MVI   DERFUNK,X'02'                                       0161 00120000
*     CALL IGFDE0(DERPLIST);        /* CANCEL ESTAE                  */ 00121000
         LA    @12,DERPLIST                                        0162 00122000
         ST    @12,@AL00001                                        0162 00123000
         L     @15,@CV00080                                        0162 00124000
         LA    @01,@AL00001                                        0162 00125000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0162 00126000
*   END;                            /* ?IGFDERR CANCEL               */ 00127000
*   XSAPTR=SAVEXSA;                 /* REFRESH XSA ADDRESS           */ 00128000
         L     XSAPTR,SAVEXSA                                      0164 00129000
*   IF DERLRC=ERROR THEN            /* IF THE ESTAE ROUTINE WAS    0165 00130000
*                                      ENTERED, THE SWAP COMMAND MUST   00131000
*                                      BE TERMINATED                 */ 00132000
         CLI   DERLRC,12                                           0165 00133000
         BNE   @RF00165                                            0165 00134000
*     DO;                           /* ESTAE WAS ENTERED             */ 00135000
*       XAE=COMABORT;               /* INDICATE COMMAND ABORTED      */ 00136000
         MVI   XAE(XSAPTR),X'3A'                                   0167 00137000
*       XAV='SWAP';                 /* INDICATE SWAP COMMAND         */ 00138000
         MVI   XAV+4(XSAPTR),C' '                                  0168 00139000
         MVC   XAV+5(3,XSAPTR),XAV+4(XSAPTR)                       0168 00140000
         MVC   XAV(4,XSAPTR),@CC01621                              0168 00141000
*     END;                                                         0169 00142000
*                                                                  0169 00143000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00144000
*   /*                                                               */ 00145000
*   /* SET UP FOR EXIT - THE ADDRESS OF THE ROUTINE TO BE ENTERED    */ 00146000
*   /* NEXT IS PUT INTO ENTRYADR (REGISTER 15), THE NORMAL RETURN    */ 00147000
*   /* ADDRESS IS PUT INTO EXITADDR (REGISTER 10), AND A PL/S RETURN */ 00148000
*   /* IS EXECUTED TO GENERATE THE PROPER EPILOG CODE - HOWEVER,     */ 00149000
*   /* CONTROL IS PASSED TO IGF2503E INSTEAD OF THE CALLING ROUTINE  */ 00150000
*   /*                                                               */ 00151000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00152000
*                                                                  0170 00153000
*   IF DERLRC=0 THEN                /* WAS AN ERROR ENCOUNTERED      */ 00154000
@RF00165 CLI   DERLRC,0                                            0170 00155000
         BNE   @RF00170                                            0170 00156000
*     ENTRYADR=SRTNADDR;            /* NO, SET UP FOR NORMAL RETURN  */ 00157000
         LR    ENTRYADR,SRTNADDR                                   0171 00158000
*   ELSE                            /* YES, ERROR DETECTED           */ 00159000
*     ENTRYADR=ADDR(IEE0503D);      /* SET UP FOR ERROR EXIT         */ 00160000
         B     @RC00170                                            0172 00161000
@RF00170 L     ENTRYADR,@CV00078                                   0172 00162000
*   EXITADDR=SRTNADDR;              /* PUT RETURN ADDRESS INTO A   0173 00163000
*                                      REGISTER                      */ 00164000
@RC00170 LR    EXITADDR,SRTNADDR                                   0173 00165000
*   RETURN TO IGF2503E CODE(ENTRYADR);/* GENERATE EPILOG CODE        */ 00166000
*                                                                  0174 00167000
         LR    @12,@15                                             0174 00168000
         L     @13,4(,@13)                                         0174 00169000
         L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0174 00170000
         LR    @01,@09                                             0174 00171000
         FREEMAIN R,LV=(0),A=(1)                                        00172000
         LR    @15,@12                                             0174 00173000
         LA    @14,IGF2503E                                        0174 00174000
         BR    @14                                                 0174 00175000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00176000
*   /*                                                               */ 00177000
*   /* AT THIS POINT, REGISTER 10 (EXITADDR) CONTAINS THE NORMAL     */ 00178000
*   /* RETURN ADDRESS AND REGISTER 15 (ENTRYADR) CONTAINS THE ACTUAL */ 00179000
*   /* EXIT ADDRESS - THE FOLLOWING CODE DOES NOT HAVE ADDRESSABILITY*/ 00180000
*   /* AND MAY ONLY MANIPULATE REGISTERS - IT COPIES THE RETURN      */ 00181000
*   /* ADDRESS INTO REGISTER 14 (RTNADDR) AND BRANCHES TO THE ADDRESS*/ 00182000
*   /* SPECIFIED IN REGISTER 15 - THIS RESULTS IN AN EXIT TO THE     */ 00183000
*   /* ORIGINAL CALLER (IEE0403D) OR TO THE SVC 34 MESSAGE WRITER    */ 00184000
*   /* (IEE0503D) (WITH REGISTER 14 STILL POINTING BACK TO IEE0403D, */ 00185000
*   /* AS REQUIRED)                                                  */ 00186000
*   /*                                                               */ 00187000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00188000
*                                                                  0175 00189000
*IGF2503E:                                                         0175 00190000
*   RTNADDR=EXITADDR;               /* SET UP RETURN ADDRESS         */ 00191000
IGF2503E LR    RTNADDR,EXITADDR                                    0175 00192000
*   GOTO NEXTRTN;                   /* EXIT TO IEE0403D OR IEE0503D  */ 00193000
         BR    ENTRYADR                                            0176 00194000
*   GENERATE NOREFS NOSETS(EJECT);                                 0177 00195000
*                                                                  0177 00196000
         EJECT                                                          00197000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00198000
*   /*                                                               */ 00199000
*   /* SUBROUTINE IGFON - PROCESSES THE 'SWAP ON' COMMAND            */ 00200000
*   /*                                                               */ 00201000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00202000
*                                                                  0178 00203000
*IGFON:                             /* SUBROUTINE ENTRY POINT        */ 00204000
*   PROCEDURE;                                                     0178 00205000
         B     @PB00002                                            0178 00206000
IGFON    STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0178 00207000
*   IF CTEXT(3:3)=' ' THEN          /* IS 'ON' FOLLOWED BY A BLANK   */ 00208000
         SR    @12,@12                                             0179 00209000
         ICM   @12,7,XAL(XSAPTR)                                   0179 00210000
         CLI   CTEXT+2(@12),C' '                                   0179 00211000
         BNE   @RF00179                                            0179 00212000
*     DO;                           /* YES, THE COMMAND IS VALID     */ 00213000
*       DERLRC=VALID;               /* INDICATE VALID SWAP COMMAND   */ 00214000
         MVI   DERLRC,X'00'                                        0181 00215000
*       CVTDDR='1'B;                /* INDICATE SYSTEM SWAPS ACTIVE  */ 00216000
         L     @12,CVTPTR                                          0182 00217000
         OI    CVTDDR(@12),B'00100000'                             0182 00218000
*     END;                                                         0183 00219000
*   ELSE                            /* NO, INVALID COMMAND           */ 00220000
*     XAE=DELERROR;                 /* INDICATE DELIMITER ERROR      */ 00221000
         B     @RC00179                                            0184 00222000
@RF00179 MVI   XAE(XSAPTR),X'07'                                   0184 00223000
*   RETURN;                         /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00224000
@EL00002 DS    0H                                                  0185 00225000
@EF00002 DS    0H                                                  0185 00226000
@ER00002 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0185 00227000
         BR    @14                                                 0185 00228000
*   END IGFON;                      /* END OF SUBROUTINE             */ 00229000
         B     @EL00002                                            0186 00230000
@PB00002 DS    0H                                                  0187 00231000
*   GENERATE NOREFS NOSETS(EJECT);                                 0187 00232000
*                                                                  0187 00233000
         EJECT                                                          00234000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00235000
*   /*                                                               */ 00236000
*   /* SUBROUTINE IGFOFF - PROCESSES THE 'SWAP OFF' COMMAND          */ 00237000
*   /*                                                               */ 00238000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00239000
*                                                                  0188 00240000
*IGFOFF:                            /* SUBROUTINE ENTRY POINT        */ 00241000
*   PROCEDURE;                                                     0188 00242000
         B     @PB00003                                            0188 00243000
IGFOFF   STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0188 00244000
*   IF CTEXT(4:4)=' ' THEN          /* IS 'OFF' FOLLOWED BY A BLANK  */ 00245000
         SR    @12,@12                                             0189 00246000
         ICM   @12,7,XAL(XSAPTR)                                   0189 00247000
         CLI   CTEXT+3(@12),C' '                                   0189 00248000
         BNE   @RF00189                                            0189 00249000
*     DO;                           /* YES, THE COMMAND IS VALID     */ 00250000
*       DERLRC=VALID;               /* INDICATE VALID SWAP COMMAND   */ 00251000
         MVI   DERLRC,X'00'                                        0191 00252000
*       CVTDDR='0'B;                /* INDICATE SYSTEM SWAPS INACTIVE*/ 00253000
         L     @12,CVTPTR                                          0192 00254000
         NI    CVTDDR(@12),B'11011111'                             0192 00255000
*     END;                                                         0193 00256000
*   ELSE                            /* NO, INVALID COMMAND           */ 00257000
*     XAE=DELERROR;                 /* INDICATE DELIMITER ERROR      */ 00258000
         B     @RC00189                                            0194 00259000
@RF00189 MVI   XAE(XSAPTR),X'07'                                   0194 00260000
*   RETURN;                         /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00261000
@EL00003 DS    0H                                                  0195 00262000
@EF00003 DS    0H                                                  0195 00263000
@ER00003 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0195 00264000
         BR    @14                                                 0195 00265000
*   END IGFOFF;                     /* END OF SUBROUTINE             */ 00266000
         B     @EL00003                                            0196 00267000
@PB00003 DS    0H                                                  0197 00268000
*   GENERATE NOREFS NOSETS(EJECT);                                 0197 00269000
*                                                                  0197 00270000
         EJECT                                                          00271000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00272000
*   /*                                                               */ 00273000
*   /* SUBROUTINE IGFSWAP - PROCESS THE 'SWAP XXX,YYY' COMMAND       */ 00274000
*   /*                                                               */ 00275000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00276000
*                                                                  0198 00277000
*IGFSWAP:                           /* SUBROUTINE ENTRY POINT        */ 00278000
*   PROCEDURE;                                                     0198 00279000
         B     @PB00004                                            0198 00280000
IGFSWAP  STM   @14,@12,@SA00004                                    0198 00281000
*   IF CTEXT(4:4)¬=','|CTEXT(8:8)¬=' ' THEN/* ARE THE DEVICE       0199 00282000
*                                      ADDRESSES SEPARATED BY A COMMA   00283000
*                                      AND FOLLOWED BY A BLANK       */ 00284000
         SR    @12,@12                                             0199 00285000
         ICM   @12,7,XAL(XSAPTR)                                   0199 00286000
         CLI   CTEXT+3(@12),C','                                   0199 00287000
         BNE   @RT00199                                            0199 00288000
         CLI   CTEXT+7(@12),C' '                                   0199 00289000
         BE    @RF00199                                            0199 00290000
@RT00199 DS    0H                                                  0200 00291000
*     XAE=DELERROR;                 /* NO, INDICATE DELIMITER ERROR  */ 00292000
         MVI   XAE(XSAPTR),X'07'                                   0200 00293000
*   ELSE                            /* YES, SYNTAX IS OK (SO FAR)    */ 00294000
*     DO;                                                          0201 00295000
*                                                                  0201 00296000
         B     @RC00199                                            0201 00297000
@RF00199 DS    0H                                                  0202 00298000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00299000
*       /*                                                           */ 00300000
*       /* INITIALIZE WORKAREA DDRCOM FOR VALIDATION REQUEST         */ 00301000
*       /*                                                           */ 00302000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00303000
*                                                                  0202 00304000
*       DDRID='DDR ';               /* PUT IN ID FIELD               */ 00305000
         MVC   DDRID(4,DDRPTR),@CC01637                            0202 00306000
*       DDROPER='1'B;               /* INDICATE OPERATOR SWAP        */ 00307000
         OI    DDROPER(DDRPTR),B'10000000'                         0203 00308000
*       DDRFMCUA=CTEXT(1:3);        /* PUT IN FROM CUA               */ 00309000
         SR    @12,@12                                             0204 00310000
         ICM   @12,7,XAL(XSAPTR)                                   0204 00311000
         MVC   DDRFMCUA(3,DDRPTR),CTEXT(@12)                       0204 00312000
*       DDRTOCUA=CTEXT(5:7);        /* PUT IN TO CUA                 */ 00313000
         MVC   DDRTOCUA(3,DDRPTR),CTEXT+4(@12)                     0205 00314000
*       DDRINV2=DDRVFM;             /* INDICATE 'FROM' VALIDATION    */ 00315000
*                                                                  0206 00316000
         MVI   DDRINV2(DDRPTR),X'01'                               0206 00317000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00318000
*       /*                                                           */ 00319000
*       /* VALIDATE THE FROM DEVICE                                  */ 00320000
*       /*                                                           */ 00321000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00322000
*                                                                  0207 00323000
*       CALL IGFDV1;                /* PERFORM VALIDATION            */ 00324000
         L     @15,@CV00081                                        0207 00325000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0207 00326000
*       DERLRC=RTNCODE;             /* COPY RETURN CODE              */ 00327000
         STC   RTNCODE,DERLRC                                      0208 00328000
*       IF DERLRC¬=0                /* DID VALIDATION FAIL           */ 00329000
*         THEN                      /* YES, DETERMINE CAUSE          */ 00330000
         CLI   DERLRC,0                                            0209 00331000
         BE    @RF00209                                            0209 00332000
*         IF DERLRC¬=ERROR THEN     /* DID A CATASTROPHIC ERROR OCCUR*/ 00333000
         CLI   DERLRC,12                                           0210 00334000
         BE    @RF00210                                            0210 00335000
*           DO;                     /* NO, DEVICE IS JUST INVALID    */ 00336000
*             XAE=ERRCODE(DDRINV1); /* CONVERT INVALID DEVICE CODE TO   00337000
*                                      ERROR CODE                    */ 00338000
         SR    @12,@12                                             0212 00339000
         IC    @12,DDRINV1(,DDRPTR)                                0212 00340000
         LA    @11,ERRCODE-1(@12)                                  0212 00341000
         MVC   XAE(1,XSAPTR),0(@11)                                0212 00342000
*             XAV=DDRFMCUA;         /* PUT DEVICE ADDRESS INTO XSA   */ 00343000
         MVI   XAV+3(XSAPTR),C' '                                  0213 00344000
         MVC   XAV+4(4,XSAPTR),XAV+3(XSAPTR)                       0213 00345000
         MVC   XAV(3,XSAPTR),DDRFMCUA(DDRPTR)                      0213 00346000
*           END;                                                   0214 00347000
*         ELSE                                                     0215 00348000
*           ;                       /* YES, CANNOT PROCESS ANY     0215 00349000
*                                      FURTHER AT THIS TIME          */ 00350000
@RF00210 DS    0H                                                  0216 00351000
*       ELSE                        /* VALIDATION WAS SUCESSFUL      */ 00352000
*         DO;                       /* SET UP TO SCHEDULE DDR        */ 00353000
*                                                                  0216 00354000
         B     @RC00209                                            0216 00355000
@RF00209 DS    0H                                                  0217 00356000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00357000
*           /*                                                       */ 00358000
*           /* COMPLETE THE FIELDS WHICH WILL BE COPIED TO THE SHORT */ 00359000
*           /* DDRCOM WHEN DDR IS SCHEDULED                          */ 00360000
*           /*                                                       */ 00361000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00362000
*                                                                  0217 00363000
*           UCBPTR=DDRFMUCB;        /* POINT TO UCB                  */ 00364000
         L     UCBPTR,DDRFMUCB(,DDRPTR)                            0217 00365000
*           DDRASID=MASTERID;       /* DDR MUST RUN IN THE MASTER  0218 00366000
*                                      SCHEDULERS ADDRESS SPACE      */ 00367000
         MVC   DDRASID(2,DDRPTR),@CH00052                          0218 00368000
*           IF DDRDA='0'B THEN      /* IS THIS A DISK SWAP           */ 00369000
         TM    DDRDA(DDRPTR),B'01000000'                           0219 00370000
         BNZ   @RF00219                                            0219 00371000
*             DDRUASID=UCBASID;     /* NO, COPY THE ADDRESS SPACE OF    00372000
*                                      THE USER                      */ 00373000
         L     @12,UCBEXTPT(,UCBPTR)                               0220 00374000
         MVC   DDRUASID(2,DDRPTR),UCBASID(@12)                     0220 00375000
*           IF DDRUASID¬=0 THEN     /* IS THERE A LOCATABLE USER OF     00376000
*                                      THE DEVICE BEING SWAPPED      */ 00377000
@RF00219 LH    @12,DDRUASID(,DDRPTR)                               0221 00378000
         LTR   @12,@12                                             0221 00379000
         BZ    @RF00221                                            0221 00380000
*             DDRUASCB=ASVTENTY(DDRUASID);/* YES, COPY THE ADDRESS OF   00381000
*                                      THE USERS ASCB                */ 00382000
         SLA   @12,2                                               0222 00383000
         L     @11,CVTPTR                                          0222 00384000
         L     @11,ASVTPTR(,@11)                                   0222 00385000
         L     @12,ASVTENTY-4(@12,@11)                             0222 00386000
         ST    @12,DDRUASCB(,DDRPTR)                               0222 00387000
*           IF DDRMT='1'B&DDRASID=0 THEN/* IS THIS A TAPE SWAP FOR A    00388000
*                                      DEVICE WHICH IS NOT IN USE    */ 00389000
@RF00221 TM    DDRMT(DDRPTR),B'00100000'                           0223 00390000
         BNO   @RF00223                                            0223 00391000
         ICM   @12,3,DDRASID(DDRPTR)                               0223 00392000
         BNZ   @RF00223                                            0223 00393000
*             DO;                   /* YES, INDICATE ERROR           */ 00394000
*               DERLRC=INVALID;     /* INDICATE INVALID SWAP         */ 00395000
         MVI   DERLRC,X'04'                                        0225 00396000
*               XAV=DDRFMCUA;       /* COPY DEVICE ADDRESS TO XSA    */ 00397000
         MVI   XAV+3(XSAPTR),C' '                                  0226 00398000
         MVC   XAV+4(4,XSAPTR),XAV+3(XSAPTR)                       0226 00399000
         MVC   XAV(3,XSAPTR),DDRFMCUA(DDRPTR)                      0226 00400000
*               XAE=NOTALOC;        /* INDICATE DEVICE NOT ALLOCATED */ 00401000
         MVI   XAE(XSAPTR),X'33'                                   0227 00402000
*             END;                                                 0228 00403000
*           ELSE                    /* NO, SWAP CAN CONTINUE         */ 00404000
*             DO;                                                  0229 00405000
         B     @RC00223                                            0229 00406000
@RF00223 DS    0H                                                  0230 00407000
*               DERLRC=VALID;       /* INDICATE VALID SWAP COMMAND   */ 00408000
*                                                                  0230 00409000
         MVI   DERLRC,X'00'                                        0230 00410000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00411000
*               /*                                                   */ 00412000
*               /* GETMAIN SPACE FOR A SHORT DDRCOM AND AN SRB -     */ 00413000
*               /* THESE BLOCKS ARE NEEDED TO SCHEDULE DDR           */ 00414000
*               /*                                                   */ 00415000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00416000
*                                                                  0231 00417000
*               DO;                 /* GETMAIN (EU) LV(LENGTH(DDRSHOR   00418000
*                                      T)+LENGTH(SRBSECT))         0231 00419000
*                                      A(DERGMADR) SP(SPN)           */ 00420000
*                 RESPECIFY                                        0232 00421000
*                  (GPR01P)RESTRICTED;                             0232 00422000
*                 I004=I004&&I004;  /* INIT LIST                     */ 00423000
         XC    I004(10),I004                                       0233 00424000
*                 I00404='00'X;     /* TYPE                          */ 00425000
         MVI   I00404,X'00'                                        0234 00426000
*                 I00401=LENGTH(DDRSHORT)+LENGTH(SRBSECT);/* LENGTH  */ 00427000
         MVC   I00401(4),@CF01661                                  0235 00428000
*                 I00403=ADDR(DERGMADR);/* ADDR OF ADDR LIST         */ 00429000
         LA    @12,DERGMADR                                        0236 00430000
         STCM  @12,7,I00403                                        0236 00431000
*                 I00405=SPN;       /* SUBPOOL VALUE                 */ 00432000
         MVI   I00405,X'F5'                                        0237 00433000
*                 GPR01P=ADDR(I004);/* REG1 POINTS TO LIST           */ 00434000
         LA    GPR01P,I004                                         0238 00435000
*                 SVC(4);           /* STANDARD-FORM OF GETMAIN      */ 00436000
         SVC   4                                                   0239 00437000
*                 RESPECIFY                                        0240 00438000
*                  (GPR01P)UNRESTRICTED;                           0240 00439000
*               END;                /* GETMAIN (EU) LV(LENGTH(DDRSHOR   00440000
*                                      T)+LENGTH(SRBSECT))         0241 00441000
*                                      A(DERGMADR) SP(SPN)           */ 00442000
*               DERGMLNG=LENGTH(DDRSHORT)+LENGTH(SRBSECT);/* INDICATE   00443000
*                                      LENGTH OF GETMAINED AREA      */ 00444000
         MVC   DERGMLNG(3),@CF01661+1                              0242 00445000
*               DERGMSPN=SPN;       /* INDICATE SUBPOOL NUMBER       */ 00446000
         MVI   DERGMSPN,X'F5'                                      0243 00447000
*               SDDRPTR=DERGMADR;   /* PICK UP ADDR OF SHORT DDRCOM  */ 00448000
*                                                                  0244 00449000
         L     SDDRPTR,DERGMADR                                    0244 00450000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00451000
*               /*                                                   */ 00452000
*               /* COPY SHORT PART OF WORKAREA DDRCOM TO SHORT DDRCOM*/ 00453000
*               /*                                                   */ 00454000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00455000
*                                                                  0245 00456000
*               SDDRPTR->DDRSHORT=DDRSHORT;/* COPY SHORT PART TO NEW    00457000
*                                      DDRCOM                        */ 00458000
         MVC   DDRSHORT(24,SDDRPTR),DDRSHORT(DDRPTR)               0245 00459000
*               SDDRPTR->DDRID='DDRS';/* INDICATE SHORT DDRCOM       */ 00460000
*                                                                  0246 00461000
         MVC   DDRID(4,SDDRPTR),@CC01646                           0246 00462000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00463000
*               /*                                                   */ 00464000
*               /* FILL IN THE SRB                                   */ 00465000
*               /*                                                   */ 00466000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00467000
*                                                                  0247 00468000
*               SRBPTR=SDDRPTR+LENGTH(DDRSHORT);/* POINT TO SRB - IT    00469000
*                                      IS IMMEDIATELY AFTER THE SHORT   00470000
*                                      DDRCOM                        */ 00471000
         LA    SRBPTR,24                                           0247 00472000
         AR    SRBPTR,SDDRPTR                                      0247 00473000
*               SRBSECT=SRBSECT&&SRBSECT;/* CLEAR THE SRB            */ 00474000
         XC    SRBSECT(44,SRBPTR),SRBSECT(SRBPTR)                  0248 00475000
*               SRBID='SRB ';       /* FILL IN SRB ID FIELD          */ 00476000
         MVC   SRBID(4,SRBPTR),@CC01647                            0249 00477000
*               SRBASCB=ASVTENTY(DDRASID);/* FILL IN ADDRESS OF THE     00478000
*                                      ASCB UNDER WHICH DDR IS TO RUN*/ 00479000
         LH    @12,DDRASID(,DDRPTR)                                0250 00480000
         SLA   @12,2                                               0250 00481000
         L     @11,CVTPTR                                          0250 00482000
         L     @11,ASVTPTR(,@11)                                   0250 00483000
         L     @12,ASVTENTY-4(@12,@11)                             0250 00484000
         ST    @12,SRBASCB(,SRBPTR)                                0250 00485000
*               SRBPARM=SDDRPTR;    /* POINT PARAMETER TO SHORT    0251 00486000
*                                      DDRCOM                        */ 00487000
*                                                                  0251 00488000
         ST    SDDRPTR,SRBPARM(,SRBPTR)                            0251 00489000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00490000
*               /*                                                   */ 00491000
*               /* FIND THE ADDRESS OF IGFDS0 TO PUT INTO THE SRB    */ 00492000
*               /*                                                   */ 00493000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00494000
*                                                                  0252 00495000
*               DO;                 /* LOAD EP('IGFDS0')             */ 00496000
*                 RESPECIFY                                        0253 00497000
*                  (GPR00P,                                        0253 00498000
*                   GPR01P)RESTRICTED;                             0253 00499000
*                 GPR00P=ADDR('IGFDS0  ');/* LOAD ENTRY POINT NAME 0254 00500000
*                                      ADDRESS                       */ 00501000
         LA    GPR00P,@CC01649                                     0254 00502000
*                 GPR01P=0;         /* JOBLIB OR LINKLIB DCB         */ 00503000
         SR    GPR01P,GPR01P                                       0255 00504000
*                 SVC(8);           /* ISSUE LOAD SVC                */ 00505000
         SVC   8                                                   0256 00506000
*                 RESPECIFY                                        0257 00507000
*                  (GPR00P,                                        0257 00508000
*                   GPR01P)UNRESTRICTED;                           0257 00509000
*               END;                /* LOAD EP('IGFDS0')             */ 00510000
*               SRBEP=LOADADDR;     /* PUT ADDRESS OF IGFDS0 INTO THE   00511000
*                                      SRB ENTRY POINT ADDRESS FIELD */ 00512000
         ST    LOADADDR,SRBEP(,SRBPTR)                             0259 00513000
*               DO;                 /* DELETE EP('IGFDS0 ')          */ 00514000
*                 RESPECIFY                                        0261 00515000
*                  (GPR00P)RESTRICTED;                             0261 00516000
*                 GPR00P=ADDR('IGFDS0  ');/* ->ENTRY NAME            */ 00517000
         LA    GPR00P,@CC01649                                     0262 00518000
*                 SVC(9);           /* DELETE SVC                    */ 00519000
         SVC   9                                                   0263 00520000
*                 RESPECIFY                                        0264 00521000
*                  (GPR00P)UNRESTRICTED;                           0264 00522000
*               END;                /* DELETE EP('IGFDS0 ')          */ 00523000
*                                                                  0265 00524000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00525000
*               /*                                                   */ 00526000
*               /* SCHEDULE THE SRB - THIS WILL CAUSE DDR TO BE      */ 00527000
*               /* ACTIVATED IN THE PROPER ADDRESS SPACE             */ 00528000
*               /*                                                   */ 00529000
*               /*****************************************************/ 00530000
*                                                                  0266 00531000
*               GENERATE REFS(SRBPTR,CVTLSMQ,SRBFLNK)              0266 00532000
*                   (SCHEDULE SRB=(SRBPTR),SCOPE=LOCAL);           0266 00533000
         SCHEDULE SRB=(SRBPTR),SCOPE=LOCAL                              00534000
*               DERGMLNG=0;         /* INDICATE AREA NO LONGER OWNED    00535000
*                                      BY IGF2503D                   */ 00536000
         SR    @12,@12                                             0267 00537000
         STCM  @12,7,DERGMLNG                                      0267 00538000
*               DERGMADR=0;         /* CLEAR ADDRESS                 */ 00539000
         ST    @12,DERGMADR                                        0268 00540000
*               DERGMSPN=0;         /* CLEAR SUBPOOL NUMBER          */ 00541000
         MVI   DERGMSPN,X'00'                                      0269 00542000
*             END;                                                 0270 00543000
*         END;                                                     0271 00544000
*     END;                                                         0272 00545000
*   RETURN;                         /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00546000
@EL00004 DS    0H                                                  0273 00547000
@EF00004 DS    0H                                                  0273 00548000
@ER00004 LM    @14,@12,@SA00004                                    0273 00549000
         BR    @14                                                 0273 00550000
*   END IGFSWAP;                    /* END OF SUBROUTINE             */ 00551000
         B     @EL00004                                            0274 00552000
*                                                                  0275 00553000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00554000
*   /*                                                               */ 00555000
*   /* ?EPILOG - GENERATE DECLARES FOR SYSTEM MACROS                 */ 00556000
*   /*                                                               */ 00557000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00558000
*                                                                  0275 00559000
*   DECLARE                         /* GENERAL PURPOSE REGISTERS     */ 00560000
*     GPR00P PTR(31)REG(0),                                        0275 00561000
*     GPR01P PTR(31)REG(1);                                        0275 00562000
*   DCL                                                            0276 00563000
*     1 I004 DEF(ILIST)BDY(WORD),   /* LIST FOR GETMAIN              */ 00564000
*      2 I00401 PTR(31),            /* LENGTH                        */ 00565000
*      2 I00402 CHAR(1),            /* HIARCHY                       */ 00566000
*      2 I00403 PTR(24),            /* ADDR OF ADDR LIST             */ 00567000
*      2 I00404 CHAR(1),            /* TYPE OF REQUEST               */ 00568000
*      2 I00405 PTR(8);             /* SUBPOOL VALUE                 */ 00569000
*   DECLARE                                                        0277 00570000
*     ILIST CHAR(10)BDY(DWORD);     /* STANDARD LIST                 */ 00571000
*   DECLARE                         /* COMMON VARIABLES              */ 00572000
*     I256C CHAR(256)BASED,                                        0278 00573000
*     I031F FIXED(31)BASED,                                        0278 00574000
*     I031P PTR(31)BASED,                                          0278 00575000
*     I015F FIXED(15)BASED,                                        0278 00576000
*     I015P PTR(15)BASED,                                          0278 00577000
*     I008P PTR(8)BASED,                                           0278 00578000
*     I001C CHAR(1)BASED;                                          0278 00579000
*   END IGF2503D                    /* END OF MODULE                 */ 00580000
*                                                                  0279 00581000

@RC00179 EQU   @EL00002                                                 02126000

         END   IGF2503D,(C'PL/S-II',0502,73318)                         02133000
./  ADD  SSI=80530130,NAME=IGF2603D
         TITLE 'IGF2603D - MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR                      *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IGF2603D CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IGF2603D  78.053'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  BALR  @11,0                                               0001 00010000
@PSTART  LA    @12,4095(,@11)                                      0001 00011000
         USING @PSTART,@11                                         0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART+4095,@12                                    0001 00013000
         L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0001 00014000
         GETMAIN  R,LV=(0)                                              00015000
         LR    @09,@01                                             0001 00016000
         USING @DATD,@09                                           0001 00017000
         ST    @13,@SA00001+4                                      0001 00018000
         LR    @13,@09                                             0001 00019000
         EJECT                                                          00020000
*                                                                  0113 00021000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00022000
*   /*                                                               */ 00023000
*   /* SAVE REGISTER 14 FOR RETURN AS NO SAVE WAS PROVIDED BY CALLER */ 00024000
*   /* AND INITIALIZE THE TEXT POINTER                               */ 00025000
*   /*                                                               */ 00026000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00027000
*                                                                  0113 00028000
*   SAVERTN=RETRNREG;                                              0113 00029000
         LR    SAVERTN,RETRNREG                                    0113 00030000
*   TEXTPTR=XAL;                                                   0114 00031000
*                                                                  0114 00032000
         MVC   TEXTPTR(3),XAL(XSAPTR)                              0114 00033000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00034000
*   /*                                                               */ 00035000
*   /* INITIALIZE VARIABLES USED BY IGF2603D                         */ 00036000
*   /*                                                               */ 00037000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00038000
*                                                                  0115 00039000
*   RETCODE=0;                      /* RETURN CODE                   */ 00040000
         SLR   @10,@10                                             0115 00041000
         STH   @10,RETCODE                                         0115 00042000
*   CPUADDR=0;                      /* CPU ADDRESS SET BY VALCPU   0116 00043000
*                                      SUBROUTINE                    */ 00044000
*                                                                  0116 00045000
         STH   @10,CPUADDR                                         0116 00046000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00047000
*   /*                                                               */ 00048000
*   /* MOVE THE IGF955I,IGF956I MESSAGE SKELETONS            @G55CP2P*/ 00049000
*   /* INTO THE 955I,956I MESSAGE BUFFERS,                   @G55CP2P*/ 00050000
*   /* CLEAR VARIABLE MESSAGE BUFFER USED TO BUILD           @G55CP2P*/ 00051000
*   /* THE VARIABLE SECTIONS OF IGF955I AND IGF953I          @G55CP2P*/ 00052000
*   /* AND INVOKE THE SYNTAX SUBROUTINE TO SYNTAX CHECK THE INPUT    */ 00053000
*   /* SUPPLIED BY THE OPERATOR IN THE MODE COMMAND                  */ 00054000
*   /*                                                               */ 00055000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00056000
*                                                                  0117 00057000
*   BUF955=MSG955;                                                 0117 00058000
         MVC   BUF955(78),MSG955                                   0117 00059000
*   VBUFMSG=' ';                    /*                       @G55CP2P*/ 00060000
         MVI   VBUFMSG+1,C' '                                      0118 00061000
         MVC   VBUFMSG+2(19),VBUFMSG+1                             0118 00062000
         MVI   VBUFMSG,C' '                                        0118 00063000
*   BUF956=MSG956;                  /*                       @G556P2P*/ 00064000
         MVC   BUF956(58),MSG956                                   0119 00065000
*   CALL SYNTAX;                                                   0120 00066000
*                                                                  0120 00067000
         BAL   @14,SYNTAX                                          0120 00068000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00069000
*   /*                                                               */ 00070000
*   /* IF THE RETURN FROM SYNTAX WAS NORMAL CONSTRUCT A DUMMY        */ 00071000
*   /* THRESHOLD BLOCK (THB) USING THE BUILDTHB SUBROUTINE           */ 00072000
*   /*                                                               */ 00073000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00074000
*                                                                  0121 00075000
*   IF RETCODE=0 THEN                                              0121 00076000
         LH    @10,RETCODE                                         0121 00077000
         LTR   @10,@10                                             0121 00078000
         BNZ   @RF00121                                            0121 00079000
*     DO;                                                          0122 00080000
*       CALL BUILDTHB;                                             0123 00081000
*                                                                  0123 00082000
         BAL   @14,BUILDTHB                                        0123 00083000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00084000
*       /*                                                           */ 00085000
*       /* IF THE THB WAS CONSTRUCTED WITHOUT ERROR THEN THE THB OF  */ 00086000
*       /* ALL ONLINE CPU'S THAT THE CHANGE WAS REQUESTED FOR WILL   */ 00087000
*       /* HAVE THEIR THB REPLACED BY THE DUMMY THB VIA THE          */ 00088000
*       /* SUBROUTINE STATCHAG                                       */ 00089000
*       /*                                                           */ 00090000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00091000
*                                                                  0124 00092000
*       IF RETCODE=0 THEN                                          0124 00093000
         LH    @10,RETCODE                                         0124 00094000
         LTR   @10,@10                                             0124 00095000
         BNZ   @RF00124                                            0124 00096000
*         CALL STATCHAG;                                           0125 00097000
         BAL   @14,STATCHAG                                        0125 00098000
*     END;                                                         0126 00099000
*                                                                  0126 00100000
@RF00124 DS    0H                                                  0127 00101000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00102000
*   /*                                                               */ 00103000
*   /* AT THIS POINT PREPERATIONS WILL BE MADE TO RETURN TO THE      */ 00104000
*   /* CALLER. IF THE XAE CONTAINS A NON-ZERO VALUE THEN IEE0503D    */ 00105000
*   /* (SVC 34 MESSAGE WRITTER) WILL BE INVOKED.                     */ 00106000
*   /*                                                               */ 00107000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00108000
*                                                                  0127 00109000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0127 00110000
*    (EXITREG,                                                     0127 00111000
*     ENTRYSAV) RSTD;                                              0127 00112000
@RF00121 DS    0H                                                  0128 00113000
*   IF XAE=0 THEN                                                  0128 00114000
         CLI   XAE(XSAPTR),0                                       0128 00115000
         BNE   @RF00128                                            0128 00116000
*     ENTRYSAV=SAVERTN;             /* NORMAL EXIT                   */ 00117000
         LR    ENTRYSAV,SAVERTN                                    0129 00118000
*   ELSE                                                           0130 00119000
*     ENTRYSAV=ADDR(IEE0503D);      /* ERROR EXIT MESSAGE WRITTER  0130 00120000
*                                      REQUIRED                      */ 00121000
*                                                                  0130 00122000
         B     @RC00128                                            0130 00123000
@RF00128 L     ENTRYSAV,@CV01921                                   0130 00124000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00125000
*   /*                                                               */ 00126000
*   /* THE RETURN ADDRESS WILL NOW ALSO BE PLACED INTO REGISTER 10 AS*/ 00127000
*   /* THE EXIT CODE WHICH FOLLOWS DOES NOT HAVE ADDRESSABILITY AND  */ 00128000
*   /* CAN ONLY MANIPULATE REGISTERS                                 */ 00129000
*   /*                                                               */ 00130000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00131000
*                                                                  0131 00132000
*   EXITREG=SAVERTN;                /* RETURN ADDRESS IN REG 10      */ 00133000
@RC00128 LR    EXITREG,SAVERTN                                     0131 00134000
*   RETURN TO EXITCODE;             /* GENERATE EPILOG CODE AND    0132 00135000
*                                      BRANCH TO EXIT ROUTINE        */ 00136000
         L     @13,4(,@13)                                         0132 00137000
         L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0132 00138000
         LR    @01,@09                                             0132 00139000
         FREEMAIN R,LV=(0),A=(1)                                        00140000
         LA    @14,EXITCODE                                        0132 00141000
         BR    @14                                                 0132 00142000
*EXITCODE:                                                         0133 00143000
*   RETRNREG=EXITREG;               /* REG 14 IS NOW SET TO RETURN TO   00144000
*                                      ORIGINAL CALLER OF IGF2603D   */ 00145000
EXITCODE LR    RETRNREG,EXITREG                                    0133 00146000
*   ENTRYREG=ENTRYSAV;              /* LOAD REG 15 WITH ENTRY POINT     00147000
*                                      ADDRESS                       */ 00148000
         LR    ENTRYREG,ENTRYSAV                                   0134 00149000
*   GOTO NEXTRTN;                   /* BRANCH TO ADDRESS SET UP IN 0135 00150000
*                                      REGISTER 15 (IEE0403D OR    0135 00151000
*                                      IEE0503D)                     */ 00152000
         BR    ENTRYREG                                            0135 00153000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0136 00154000
*    (EXITREG,                                                     0136 00155000
*     ENTRYSAV) UNRSTD;                                            0136 00156000
*   GEN(EJECT);                                                    0137 00157000
         EJECT                                                          00158000
*                                                                  0138 00159000
*/*     STATCHAG - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D) 0138 00160000
*                                                                  0138 00161000
*       THIS SUBROUTINE IS INVOKED BY MAINLINE OF THE MODE COMMAND 0138 00162000
*       PROCESSOR. IT HAS TWO FUNCTIONS.                           0138 00163000
*                                                                  0138 00164000
*       ONE FUNCTION IS TO REPLACE THE THRESHOLD BLOCKS OF         0138 00165000
*       THE CPU'S SPECIFIED IN THE MODE COMMAND WITH THE DUMMY THRESHOL 00166000
*       BLOCK CONSTRUCTED BY THE BUILDTHB SUBROUTINE.  IF THE CPU=ALL   00167000
*       WAS SPECIFIED OR DEFAULTED THEN THE THRESHOLD BLOCK IN THE RWA  00168000
*       WILL ALSO BE REPLACED. IF THE THRESHOLD BLOCK TO BE REPLACED    00169000
*       IS A SR OR DG THRESHOLD BLOCK, THEN EACH SPECIFIED PROCESSOR    00170000
*       IS SIGNALED TO UPDATE CONTROL REGISTERS.                   0138 00171000
*                                                            @G556P2P   00172000
*       THE OTHER FUNCTION IS TO SET A BIT (PWAENABL) REQUESTING   0138 00173000
*       IGFPEXIT TO ENABLE THE HIGH SPEED BUFFER AND TLB  (MODELS  0138 00174000
*       168 AND 165-II ONLY) IN RESPONSE TO THE ENABLE KEYWORD ON  0138 00175000
*       THE MODE COMMAND. EACH SPECIFIED PROCESSOR IS SIGNALED TO  0138 00176000
*       PERFORM THE DESIRED FUNCTION.                              0138 00177000
*                                                                  0138 00178000
*       IN BOTH CASES A WTO IS ISSUED TO INFORM THE OPERATOR OF THE     00179000
*       ACTION TAKEN BY THE MODE COMMAND.                          0138 00180000
*                                                                  0138 00181000
*                                                                  0138 00182000
*       THE EXTERNAL PROCEDURE CALLING THIS SUBROUTINE MUST:       0138 00183000
*          1. HAVE SET THE VARIABLES 'EVENTID' AND 'CPUADDR'.      0138 00184000
*          2. HAVE PROVIDED AN 18 WORD REGISTER SAVE AREA WHOSE ADDRESS 00185000
*             IS IN REGISTER 13 AT ENTRY TO THIS SUBROUTINE.       0138 00186000
*          3. HAVE DECLARED THE STRUCTURES 'CPUSW', 'EVENTSW'      0138 00187000
*             AND THE VARIABLE 'RETCODE'.                          0138 00188000
*                                                                  0138 00189000
*                                                                  0138 00190000
*       AT EXIT ALL REGISTERS ARE RETURNED TO THE CALLER UNCHANGED.     00191000
*                                                                  0138 00192000
*                                                                    */ 00193000
*                                                                  0138 00194000
*STATCHAG:                                                         0138 00195000
*   PROC;                                                          0138 00196000
*                                                                  0138 00197000
         B     @PB00002                                            0138 00198000
STATCHAG STM   @14,@07,@SA00002                                    0138 00199000
         STM   @09,@12,@SA00002+40                                 0138 00200000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00201000
*   /*                                                               */ 00202000
*   /* INTERNAL DECLARES                                             */ 00203000
*   /*                                                               */ 00204000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00205000
*                                                                  0139 00206000
*   DCL                                                            0139 00207000
*     RTNCDREG FIXED(31) REG(15);   /* RPSGNL RETURN CODE REG        */ 00208000
*   DCL                                                            0140 00209000
*     REGONE FIXED(31) REG(1) RSTD; /* REGISTER 1 DECLARE            */ 00210000
*   DCL                                                            0141 00211000
*     1 EXITSAVE BDY(DWORD),        /* SAVE AREA FOR PEXIT           */ 00212000
*      2 REGSAVE CHAR(64),          /* REGISTER SAVE AREA            */ 00213000
*      2 RTNPSW CHAR(8) BDY(DWORD), /* RETURN PSW                    */ 00214000
*       3 SYSMASK CHAR(1),          /* SYSTEM MASK                   */ 00215000
*       3 KEYMASK CHAR(1),          /* PROTECTION KEY AND MASK       */ 00216000
*       3 * CHAR(2),                                               0141 00217000
*       3 RTNADDR PTR(31);          /* RETURN ADDRESS FOR PEXIT      */ 00218000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0142 00219000
*    (I,                                                           0142 00220000
*     CPUALREG) RSTD;                                              0142 00221000
*                                                                  0142 00222000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00223000
*   /*                                                               */ 00224000
*   /* DETERMINE IF CPU=ALL WAS SPECIFIED OR DEFAULTED (CPUID = 1)   */ 00225000
*   /*                                                               */ 00226000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00227000
*                                                                  0143 00228000
*   IF CPUID=ALLCPUS                                               0143 00229000
*                                                                  0143 00230000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00231000
*   /*                                                               */ 00232000
*   /* UPDATE THE REQUIRED RWA THRESHOLD BLOCK                       */ 00233000
*   /*                                                               */ 00234000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00235000
*                                                                  0143 00236000
*     THEN                                                         0143 00237000
         CLI   CPUID,1                                             0143 00238000
         BNE   @RF00143                                            0143 00239000
*     DO;                           /* CPU=ALL                       */ 00240000
*       IF EVENTID=RECVRY THEN                                     0145 00241000

*       /*************************************************************/ 00334000
*       /*                                                           */ 00335000
*       /* INITIALIZE LOOP INDEX AND LOOP CONTROL                    */ 00336000
*       /*                                                           */ 00337000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00338000
*                                                                  0161 00339000
*       I=0;                                                       0161 00340000
@RF00159 DS    0H                                                  0161 00341000
@RC00157 DS    0H                                                  0161 00342000
@RC00155 DS    0H                                                  0161 00343000
@RC00153 DS    0H                                                  0161 00344000
@RC00151 DS    0H                                                  0161 00345000
@RC00149 DS    0H                                                  0161 00346000
@RC00147 DS    0H                                                  0161 00347000
@RC00145 SLR   I,I                                                 0161 00348000
*       SINGLCPU=BITOFF;                                           0162 00349000
         NI    SINGLCPU,B'10111111'                                0162 00350000
*     END;                                                         0163 00351000
*                                                                  0163 00352000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00353000
*   /*                                                               */ 00354000
*   /* IF A SINGLE CPU WAS SPECIFIED SET THE LOOP INDEX TO THE CPU   */ 00355000
*   /* VALUE AND SET THE SINGLE CPU FLAG                             */ 00356000
*   /*                                                               */ 00357000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00358000
*                                                                  0164 00359000
*   ELSE                                                           0164 00360000
*     DO;                                                          0164 00361000
         B     @RC00143                                            0164 00362000
@RF00143 DS    0H                                                  0165 00363000
*       I=CPUADDR;                                                 0165 00364000
         LH    I,CPUADDR                                           0165 00365000
*       SINGLCPU=BITON;                                            0166 00366000
         OI    SINGLCPU,B'01000000'                                0166 00367000
*     END;                                                         0167 00368000
*                                                                  0167 00369000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00370000
*   /*                                                               */ 00371000
*   /* A TEST WILL NOW BE MADE TO DETERMINE IF THE CPU(S) SPECIFIED  */ 00372000
*   /* ARE ON LINE. IF ON LINE THE VARIABLE 'PCCAPTR' WILL BE SET TO */ 00373000
*   /* POINT TO THE PCCA OF THE REQUESTED CPU. THE THB IS LOCATED AND*/ 00374000
*   /* UPDATED. IF BUFFER/TLB UPDATING IS REQUESTED, A BIT IN THE PWA*/ 00375000
*   /* OF THE REQUESTED CPU IS SET. IF THE THRESHOLD BLOCK IS A SR OR*/ 00376000
*   /* DG THRESHOLD BLOCK, A SIGP WILL BE ISSUED TO CAUSE THE CPU'S  */ 00377000
*   /* CONTROL REGISTERS TO BE UPDATED AND/OR TO CAUSE ENABLEMENT OF */ 00378000
*   /* THAT CPU'S BUFFER/TLB                                 @G556P2P*/ 00379000
*   /*                                                               */ 00380000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00381000
*                                                                  0168 00382000
*   DO WHILE I¬>CVTMAXMP;                                          0168 00383000
@RC00143 B     @DE00168                                            0168 00384000
@DL00168 DS    0H                                                  0169 00385000
*     CPUALREG=CSDCPUAL;            /* OBTAIN BIT MASK OF ONLINE   0169 00386000
*                                      CPU'S                         */ 00387000

         L     @07,CVTCSD(,@07)                                    0169 00389000
         LH    CPUALREG,CSDCPUAL(,@07)                             0169 00390000
         N     CPUALREG,@CF02044                                   0169 00391000
*     GEN REFS(I) SETS(CPUALREG)(SLL CPUALREG,16(I));/* SHIFT LEFT BY   00392000
*                                      I                             */ 00393000
*                                                                  0170 00394000
         SLL CPUALREG,16(I)                                             00395000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00396000
*     /*                                                             */ 00397000
*     /* IF THE REGISTER CPUALREG CONTAINES A NEGATIVE VALUE THEN THE*/ 00398000
*     /* CPU WAS ON LINE AND PROCESSING CONTINUES. IF NOT NEGATIVE   */ 00399000
*     /* THEN THE NEXT PROCESSOR WILL BE CHECKED UNTIL ALL CPU'S     */ 00400000
*     /* SPECIFIED HAVE BEEN TESTED                                  */ 00401000
*     /*                                                             */ 00402000
*     /***************************************************************/ 00403000
*                                                                  0171 00404000
*     IF CPUALREG<0 THEN                                           0171 00405000
         LTR   CPUALREG,CPUALREG                                   0171 00406000
         BNM   @RF00171                                            0171 00407000
*       DO;                                                        0172 00408000
*         PCCAPTR=PCCAT00P(I+1);                                   0173 00409000
*                                                                  0173 00410000

*         /***********************************************************/ 00416000
*         /*                                                         */ 00417000
*         /* DETERMINE IF BUFFER/TLB IS TO BE ENABLED- IF SO, SET BIT*/ 00418000
*         /* TO REQUEST ENABLE                               @G556P2P*/ 00419000
*         /*                                                         */ 00420000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00421000
*                                                                  0174 00422000
*         IF DUMYENAB¬=0            /* IS ENABLE IN ORDER    @G556P2P*/ 00423000
*           THEN                                                   0174 00424000

*           DO;                     /* YES - SET PWA TO      @G556P2P*/ 00427000
*             PWAENABL='1'B;        /* REQUEST BUFF/TLB      @G556P2P*/ 00428000

*           END;                    /* ENABLE                @G556P2P*/ 00431000
*                                                                  0177 00432000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00433000
*         /*                                                         */ 00434000
*         /* DETERMINE THRESHOLD BLOCK TO BE UPDATED, SET THE        */ 00435000

*         /***********************************************************/ 00440000
*                                                                  0178 00441000

*             EVENT955='SR';                                       0181 00451000

*                                                                  0217 00552000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00553000
*         /*                                                         */ 00554000

*         /*                                                         */ 00556000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00557000
*                                                                  0218 00558000

*           THEN                                                   0218 00560000

@RC00208 DS    0H                                                  0218 00562000
@RC00203 DS    0H                                                  0218 00563000
@RC00198 DS    0H                                                  0218 00564000
@RC00193 DS    0H                                                  0218 00565000
@RC00188 DS    0H                                                  0218 00566000
@RC00183 DS    0H                                                  0218 00567000
@RC00178 CLI   EVENTID,3                                           0218 00568000

         BE    @RF00218                                            0218 00571000

*                                                                  0275 00826000
*/*     SYNTAX - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D)   0275 00827000
*                                                                  0275 00828000
*       THIS SUBROUTINE IS INVOKED BY MAINLINE OF THE MODE COMMAND 0275 00829000
*       PROCESSOR ITS FUNCTION IS TO SYNTAX CHECK THE INPUT SUPPLIED BY 00830000
*       THE OPERATOR AND CALL THE NECESSARY SUBROUTINES TO PERFORM THE  00831000
*       OPERATION REQUESTED BY THE MODE COMMAND.  THE SUBROUTINES THAT  00832000
*       MAY BE CALLED BY SYNTAX ARE MODESTAT, FINDEL, WTO958I,WTO959I,  00833000
*       AND ENDTEXT.  THE FOLLOWING RETURN CODES ARE SET BY SYNTAX:     00834000
*                 0 - NORMAL RETURN INDICATING SYNTAX WAS CORRECT AND   00835000
*                     PROCESSING SHOULD CONTINUE IN MAINLINE       0275 00836000
*                 4 - ONLY STATUS WAS REQUESTED AND IT HAS BEEN GIVEN   00837000
*                 8 - AN INVALID CHARACTER OR VALUE WAS DETECTED IN     00838000
*                     THE CPU=X , RECORD=N , ENABLE=N , INTERVAL=N ,    00839000
*                     OR REPORT=N VERB.  TERMINATE PROCESSING      0275 00840000
*                     IN MAINLINE.                                 0275 00841000
*                 12- AN INVALID DELIMITER HAS BEEN DETECTED. TERMINATE 00842000
*                     PROCESSING IN MAINLINE.                      0275 00843000
*                 16- OTHER VERB(S) ISSUED ALONG WITH STATUS       0275 00844000
*                 20- INVALID VERB FOUND AND WTO958I SUBROUTINE WAS     00845000
*                     INVOKED.                                     0275 00846000
*                 24- ENABLE FUNCTION INVALID FOR CPU MODEL  @G556P2P   00847000
*                                                                  0275 00848000
*                                                                  0275 00849000
*       THE EXTERNAL PROCEDURE CALLING THIS SUBROUTINE MUST:       0275 00850000
*          1. HAVE SET THE VARIABLE 'TEXTPTR' TO POINT TO THE BEGINNING 00851000
*             OF THE TEXT TO BE CHECKED.                           0275 00852000
*          2. HAVE PROVIDED AN 18 WORD REGISTER SAVE AREA WHOSE ADDRESS 00853000
*             IS IN REGISTER 13 AT ENTRY TO THIS SUBROUTINE.       0275 00854000
*          3. HAVE DECLARED THE STRUCTURES 'CPUSW', 'EVENTSW' AND  0275 00855000
*             'MODESW' AND THE VARIABLE 'RETCODE'.                 0275 00856000
*                                                                  0275 00857000
*                                                                  0275 00858000
*                                                                  0275 00859000
*                                                                    */ 00860000
*                                                                  0275 00861000
*SYNTAX:                                                           0275 00862000
*   PROC;                                                          0275 00863000
*                                                                  0275 00864000
         B     @PB00003                                            0275 00865000

*   /*****************************************************************/ 00868000
*   /*                                                               */ 00869000
*   /* INITIALIZE LOOP CONTROL SWITCH                                */ 00870000

*   /*****************************************************************/ 00872000
*                                                                  0276 00873000
*   ENDBIT=BITOFF;                                                 0276 00874000
*                                                                  0276 00875000
         NI    ENDBIT,B'01111111'                                  0276 00876000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00877000
*   /*                                                               */ 00878000
