*                                                                  0277 00882000
*   IF TEXTPTR=0 THEN                                              0277 00883000

         LTR   @10,@10                                             0277 00886000
         BNZ   @RF00277                                            0277 00887000
*     DO;                                                          0278 00888000
*                                                                  0278 00889000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00890000

*       /* DEFAULT IS STATUS. CALL MODESTAT SUBROUTINE, SET RETURN   */ 00892000

*       /*                                                           */ 00894000

*                                                                  0279 00896000

*         /***********************************************************/ 00941000
*         /*                                                         */ 00942000

*         /* ERROR IS ENCOUNTERED                                    */ 00944000
*         /*                                                         */ 00945000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00946000
*                                                                  0295 00947000

*         /***********************************************************/ 00951000

*         /*                                                         */ 00954000

*         /*                                                         */ 00961000
*         /* IF RETURN CODE FROM FINDEL SUBROUTINE = 4 THEN INVOKE   */ 00962000
*         /* WTO958I SUBROUTINE TO INFORM THE OPERATOR THAT AN       */ 00963000
*         /* INVALID VERB WAS ISSUED, SET THE RETURN CODE = 20 AND   */ 00964000
*         /* RETURN TO CALLER                                        */ 00965000
*         /*                                                         */ 00966000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00967000
*                                                                  0297 00968000
*         IF RETCODE=4 THEN                                        0297 00969000

*           DO;                                                    0298 00972000

*             RETCODE=20;                                          0300 00975000

*           END;                                                   0301 00977000
*                                                                  0301 00978000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00979000
*         /*                                                         */ 00980000
*         /* IF RETURN CODE WAS NOT 4 THEN CHECK FOR ZERO. IF NOT    */ 00981000
*         /* ZERO THEN AN INVALID CHARACTER WAS SPECIFIED IN THE     */ 00982000
*         /* CPU=X , RECORD=N , ENABLE=N , INTERVAL=N, OR REPORT=N   */ 00983000
*         /* VERB (RETURN CODE = 8) OR A CONFLICTING VERB WAS        */ 00984000
*         /* SPECIFIED (RETURN CODE = 12). IN THIS CASE THE RETURN   */ 00985000
*         /* CODE IS SET TO EIGHT AND CONTROL IS RETURNED TO THE     */ 00986000
*         /* CALLER                                                  */ 00987000
*         /*                                                         */ 00988000
*         /***********************************************************/ 00989000
*                                                                  0302 00990000
*         ELSE                                                     0302 00991000
*           IF RETCODE¬=0 THEN                                     0302 00992000
         B     @RC00297                                            0302 00993000
@RF00297 LH    @10,RETCODE                                         0302 00994000
         LTR   @10,@10                                             0302 00995000
         BZ    @RF00302                                            0302 00996000
*             RETCODE=8;                                           0303 00997000
*                                                                  0303 00998000
         MVC   RETCODE(2),@CH00048                                 0303 00999000
*         /***********************************************************/ 01000000
*         /*                                                         */ 01001000
*         /* IF RETURN CODE IS ZERO THEN VERB SPECIFIED IS OK. THE   */ 01002000
*         /* ENDTEXT SUBROUTINE WILL NOW BE INVOKED TO LOCATE THE    */ 01003000
*         /* NEXT VERB OR END OF TEXT.                               */ 01004000
*         /*                                                         */ 01005000
*         /***********************************************************/ 01006000
*                                                                  0304 01007000
*           ELSE                                                   0304 01008000
*             DO;                                                  0304 01009000
         B     @RC00302                                            0304 01010000
@RF00302 DS    0H                                                  0305 01011000
*               CALL ENDTEXT;                                      0305 01012000
*                                                                  0305 01013000
         BAL   @14,ENDTEXT                                         0305 01014000
*               /*****************************************************/ 01015000
*               /*                                                   */ 01016000
*               /* THE RETURN CODE FROM ENDTEXT WILL NOW BE CHECKED. */ 01017000

*/*     ELBAIRAV - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D) 0344 01288000
*                                                                  0344 01289000
*       THIS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED WHEN A VARIABLE LENGTH VERB HAS BEEN  01290000

*   GEN(EJECT);                                                    0371 01449000

*/*    ENDTEXT - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D)   0372 01452000
*                                                                  0372 01453000
*      THIS SUBROUTINE IS USED TO LOCATE THE END OF TEXT OR THE NEXT    01454000
*      VERB IN THE MODE COMMAND.  UPON ENTRY TO THIS SUBROUTINE THE     01455000
*      VARIABLE 'TEXTPTR' MUST POINT TO THE NEXT CHARACTER AFTER THE    01456000
*      VERB JUST PROCESSED BY THE CALLER.  THIS CHARACTER IS THEN  0372 01457000
*      CHECKED FOR A COMMA OR A BLANK.  IF A COMMA THEN A 1 IS ADDED TO 01458000
*      'TEXTPTR', A RETURN CODE IS SET AND CONTROL IS RETURNED TO THE   01459000
*      CALLER. IF A BLANK THEN THE FOLLOWING CHARACTER IS CHECKED FOR A 01460000
*      BLANK.  IF THIS CHARACTER IS A BLANK THEN A RETURN CODE IS SET T 01461000
*      INDICATE END OF TEXT AND CONTROL IS RETURNED TO THE CALLER.  IF  01462000
*      THIS CHARACTER WAS NOT A BLANK THEN THE ACTION IS THE SAME AS    01463000
*      WITH A COMMA AS DESCRIBED ABOVE.  IF THE FIRST CHARACTER WAS NOT 01464000
*      A COMMA OR A BLANK THEN A RETURN CODE IS SET TO INDICATE AN 0372 01465000
*      INVALID DELIMITER AND CONTROL IS RETURNED TO THE CALLER.    0372 01466000
*      THE RETURN CODES ARE SET AS FOLLOWS:                        0372 01467000
*            0 - END OF TEXT HAS BEEN FOUND                        0372 01468000
*            4 - 'TEXTPTR' HAS BEEN UPDATED TO POINT TO NEXT VERB  0372 01469000
*            8 - AN INVALID DELIMITER HAS BEEN FOUND               0372 01470000
*                                                                  0372 01471000
*      THE EXTERNAL PROCEDURE CALLING THIS SUBROUTINE MUST:        0372 01472000
*         1. HAVE SET THE VARIABLE 'TEXTPTR' TO POINT TO THE CHARACTER  01473000
*            TO BE CHECKED.                                        0372 01474000
*         2. HAVE PROVIDED AN 18 WORD REGISTER SAVE AREA WHOSE ADDRESS  01475000
*            IS IN REGISTER 13 AT ENTRY TO THIS SUBROUTINE.        0372 01476000
*         3. HAVE DECLARED THE VARIABLES 'INPUTEXT' BASED(TEXTPTR) AND  01477000
*            'RETCODE'.                                            0372 01478000
*         4. HAVE PROVIDED A DESECT FOR THE XSA                    0372 01479000
*                                                                  0372 01480000
*                                                                  0372 01481000
*                                                                  0372 01482000
*                                                                    */ 01483000
*                                                                  0372 01484000
*ENDTEXT:                                                          0372 01485000
*   PROC;                                                          0372 01486000
*                                                                  0372 01487000
         B     @PB00005                                            0372 01488000
ENDTEXT  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0372 01489000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 01490000
*   /*                                                               */ 01491000
*   /* INITIALLY SET THE RETURN CODE TO FOUR                         */ 01492000
*   /*                                                               */ 01493000

*                                                                  0373 01495000

*   /*****************************************************************/ 01499000
*   /*                                                               */ 01500000
*   /* DETERMINE IF NEXT CHARACTER IS A COMMA. IF SO ADD 1 TO        */ 01501000
*   /* 'TEXTPTR' AND RETURN                                          */ 01502000
*   /*                                                               */ 01503000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 01504000
*                                                                  0374 01505000
*   IF INPUTEXT(1)=',' THEN                                        0374 01506000

*   /* '07'X, SET THE RETURN CODE TO 8 AND RETURN                    */ 01518000

*                                                                  0376 01521000

*/*    BUILDTHB - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D)  0384 01556000
*                                                                  0384 01557000
*      THIS SUBROUTINE INTERPRETS THE EVENT VERB AND THE CPU VERB  0384 01558000
*      OF THE MODE COMMAND ISSUED BY THE OPERATOR AND AND CONSTRUCTS A  01559000
*      DUMMY THRESHOLD BLOCK (THB) AS PER THE VERBS SPECIFIED OR   0384 01560000

*                                                                  0384 01576000
*                                                                  0384 01577000

*/*     MODESTAT - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D) 0511 02162000
*                                                                  0511 02163000
*       THIS SUBROUTINE WILL OBTAIN THE STATUS OF THE DIFFERENT    0511 02164000
*       EVENTS FROM THE THB'S   OF ALL ON LINE CPU'S AND TRANSFER  0511 02165000
*       CONTROL TO THE SUBROUTINE KNOWN AS VALTHB TO CONVERT THE STATUS 02166000
*       TO PRINTABLE CHARACTERS AND OUTPUT SAME TO THE OPERATOR.   0511 02167000
*       VALTHB WILL BE CALLED FOR EACH ONLINE CPU, ONCE EACH FOR   0511 02168000
*       DG,SR,PD,SD,IV,TC,PT, AND CC.                        @G55CP2P   02169000
*                                                                  0511 02170000
*                                                                  0511 02171000

*                                                                  0511 02179000

*MODESTAT:                                                         0511 02182000
*   PROC;                                                          0511 02183000
*                                                                  0511 02184000

MODESTAT STM   @14,@07,@SA00008                                    0511 02186000
         STM   @09,@12,@SA00008+40                                 0511 02187000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02188000
*   /*                                                               */ 02189000
*   /* INTERNAL DECLARES                                             */ 02190000
*   /*                                                               */ 02191000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02192000
*                                                                  0512 02193000
*   DCL                                                            0512 02194000
*     CPUFIELD CHAR(2) BDY(HWORD);  /* FIELD FOR CPU ADDRESS       0512 02195000
*                                      CONVERSION                    */ 02196000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0513 02197000
*    (I,                                                           0513 02198000
*     CPUALREG) RESTRICTED;                                        0513 02199000
*                                                                  0513 02200000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02201000
*   /*                                                               */ 02202000
*   /* MOVE MESSAGE SKELETON INTO MESSAGE BUFFER                     */ 02203000
*   /*                                                               */ 02204000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02205000
*                                                                  0514 02206000
*   BUF953=MSG953;                                                 0514 02207000
*                                                                  0514 02208000
         MVC   BUF953(76),MSG953                                   0514 02209000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02210000
*   /*                                                               */ 02211000
*   /* OBTAIN STATUS FOR ALL CPU'S ON LINE UP TO THE MAXIMUM NUMBER  */ 02212000
*   /* OF CPU'S HANDELED BY THIS RELEASE                             */ 02213000
*   /*                                                               */ 02214000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02215000
*                                                                  0515 02216000
*   DO I=0 TO CVTMAXMP;                                            0515 02217000
*                                                                  0515 02218000

         B     @DE00515                                            0515 02220000
@DL00515 DS    0H                                                  0516 02221000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02222000
*     /*                                                             */ 02223000
*     /* DETERMINE IF THIS CPU IS ON LINE BY CHECKING CPU ALIVE BIT  */ 02224000
*     /* IN THE CSD. IF ON LINE SET 'PCCAPTR' TO THE ADDRESS OF THIS */ 02225000
*     /* CPU'S PCCA                                                  */ 02226000
*     /*                                                             */ 02227000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02228000
*                                                                  0516 02229000
*     CPUALREG=CSDCPUAL;            /* OBTAIN BIT MASK OF ACTIVE   0516 02230000
*                                      CPU'S                         */ 02231000
         L     @01,CVTPTR                                          0516 02232000
         L     @01,CVTCSD(,@01)                                    0516 02233000
         LH    CPUALREG,CSDCPUAL(,@01)                             0516 02234000
         N     CPUALREG,@CF02044                                   0516 02235000
*     GEN REFS(I) SETS(CPUALREG)(SLL CPUALREG,16(I));/* MOVE BIT   0517 02236000
*                                      DESIRED TO REGISTER SIGN BIT  */ 02237000
         SLL CPUALREG,16(I)                                             02238000
*     IF CPUALREG<0 THEN                                           0518 02239000
         LTR   CPUALREG,CPUALREG                                   0518 02240000
         BNM   @RF00518                                            0518 02241000
*       DO;                                                        0519 02242000
*         PCCAPTR=PCCAT00P(I+1);    /* OBTAIN ADDRESS OF PCCA        */ 02243000
*                                                                  0520 02244000
         LR    @01,I                                               0520 02245000
         SLA   @01,2                                               0520 02246000
         L     @07,CVTPTR                                          0520 02247000
         L     @07,CVTPCCAT(,@07)                                  0520 02248000
         L     PCCAPTR,PCCAT00P(@01,@07)                           0520 02249000
*         /***********************************************************/ 02250000
*         /*                                                         */ 02251000
*         /* CONVERT CPU ADDRESS TO EBCDIC                   @G55CP2P*/ 02252000
*         /*                                                         */ 02253000
*         /***********************************************************/ 02254000
*                                                                  0521 02255000
*         CPUFIELD=PCCACPUA+'F0'X;                                 0521 02256000
         LA    @01,240                                             0521 02257000

*   GEN(EJECT);                                                    0555 02430000
         EJECT                                                          02431000
*                                                                  0556 02432000
*/*     FINDEL - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D)   0556 02433000
*                                                                  0556 02434000
*       THIS SUBROUTINE WILL COMPARE THE VERBS SUPPLIED BY THE OPERATOR 02435000
*       IN THE MODE COMMAND AGAINST       TABLES WHICH CONTAIN ALL OF   02436000
*       THE VALID VERBS.  THE VERB POINTED TO BY 'TEXTPTR' WILL BE 0556 02437000
*       COMPARED WITH THE TABLES UNTIL A. ALL TABLES HAVE BEEN CHECKED  02438000
*       B. A COMPARSION IS FOUND OR C. AN ERROR IS DETECTED.  IF A 0556 02439000
*       VARIABLE LENGTH    VERB WAS FOUND THE ELBAIRAV SUBROUTINE WILL  02440000
*       BE CALLED TO PROCESS IT.  IF A VALID VERB WAS FOUND THE VARIABL 02441000
*       'TEXTPTR' WILL BE UPDATED TO POINT TO THE NEXT CHARACTER AFTER  02442000
*       THE VERB JUST CHECKED.  THE FINDEL SUBROUTINE WILL SET THE 0556 02443000
*       FOLLOWING RETURN CODES:                                    0556 02444000
*            0 - NORMAL RETURN, VERB SUPPLIED IS VALID             0556 02445000
*            4 - INVALID VERB SUPPLIED                             0556 02446000
*            8 - INVALID FIELD IN THE VARIABLE LENGTH   VERB       0556 02447000
*            12- CONFLICTING VERBS SUPPLIED                        0556 02448000
*                                                                  0556 02449000
*       THE EXTERNAL PROCEDURE CALLING THIS SUBROUTINE MUST:       0556 02450000
*          1. HAVE PROVIDED AN 18 WORD REGISTER SAVE AREA WHOSE ADDRESS 02451000
*             IS IN REGISTER 13 AT ENTRY TO THIS SUBROUTINE.       0556 02452000
*          2. HAVE PROVIDED VERB TABLES KNOWN AS 'EVENTAB', 'CPUIDTAB'  02453000
*             AND 'MODETAB'.  ALSO STRUCTURES KNOWN AS 'EVENTSW',  0556 02454000
*             'CPUSW','MODESW','INTVSW','ENABSW', AND 'REPTSW'.    0556 02455000
*          3.  HAVE SET THE VARIABLE 'TEXTPTR' TO POINT TO THE VERB TO  02456000
*              BE CHECKED.                                         0556 02457000
*          4.  HAVE DECLARED A VARIABLE KNOWN AS 'RETCODE'.        0556 02458000
*                                                                  0556 02459000
*                                                                  0556 02460000
*                                                                  0556 02461000
*                                                                  0556 02462000
*                                                                    */ 02463000
*                                                                  0556 02464000
*FINDEL:                                                           0556 02465000
*   PROC;                                                          0556 02466000
*                                                                  0556 02467000
         B     @PB00009                                            0556 02468000
FINDEL   STM   @14,@12,@SA00009                                    0556 02469000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02470000
*   /*                                                               */ 02471000
*   /* FINDEL INTERNAL DECLARES                                      */ 02472000
*   /*                                                               */ 02473000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02474000
*                                                                  0557 02475000
*   DCL                                                            0557 02476000
*     1 TABSCAN BASED(TABADDR),     /* OVERLAY FOR TABLE TO BE     0557 02477000
*                                      SEARCHED                      */ 02478000
*      2 TABLENGH PTR(15),          /* LENGTH OF TABLE               */ 02479000
*      2 TABDATA(*),                                               0557 02480000
*       3 VARYFLAG BIT(8),          /* FLAG TO INDICATE VARIABLE   0557 02481000
*                                      LENGTH ELEMENT                */ 02482000
*       3 ELEMSIZE BIT(8),          /* LENGTH OF ELEMENT             */ 02483000
*       3 ELEMENT CHAR(12);                                        0557 02484000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0558 02485000
*    (I,                                                           0558 02486000
*     J) RSTD;                      /* RESTRICT LOOP CONTROL       0558 02487000
*                                      REGISTERS                     */ 02488000
*                                                                  0558 02489000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02490000
*   /*                                                               */ 02491000
*   /* DECLARES FOR ARRAY OF TABLE ADDRESSES                         */ 02492000
*   /*                                                               */ 02493000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02494000
*                                                                  0559 02495000
*   DCL                                                            0559 02496000
*     TABLEPTR(6) PTR(31) LOCAL INIT(ADDR(EVENTTAB),ADDR(CPUIDTAB),ADDR 02497000
*         (MODETAB),                /*                       @G55CP2P*/ 02498000
*         ADDR(INTVTAB),ADDR(REPTTAB),ADDR(ENABTAB));/*      @G55CP2P*/ 02499000
*                                                                  0559 02500000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02501000
*   /*                                                               */ 02502000
*   /* DECLARE FOR ARRAY OF SWITCH ADDRESSES                         */ 02503000
*   /*                                                               */ 02504000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02505000
*                                                                  0560 02506000

*     SWTCHPTR(DIM(TABLEPTR)) PTR(31);                             0560 02508000
*                                                                  0560 02509000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02510000
*   /*                                                               */ 02511000

*   /*                                                               */ 02513000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02514000
*                                                                  0561 02515000
*   SWTCHPTR(1)=ADDR(EVENTSW);                                     0561 02516000
         LA    @10,EVENTSW                                         0561 02517000
         ST    @10,SWTCHPTR                                        0561 02518000
*   SWTCHPTR(2)=ADDR(CPUSW);                                       0562 02519000
         LA    @10,CPUSW                                           0562 02520000
         ST    @10,SWTCHPTR+4                                      0562 02521000
*   SWTCHPTR(3)=ADDR(MODESW);                                      0563 02522000

*   SWTCHPTR(4)=ADDR(INTVSW);       /*                       @G55CP2P*/ 02525000

*   SWTCHPTR(5)=ADDR(REPTSW);       /*                       @G556P2P*/ 02528000

*   SWTCHPTR(6)=ADDR(ENABSW);       /*                       @G556P2P*/ 02531000
*                                                                  0566 02532000
         LA    @10,ENABSW                                          0566 02533000
         ST    @10,SWTCHPTR+20                                     0566 02534000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02535000
*   /*                                                               */ 02536000
*   /* SEARCH THE TABLES UNTIL COMPARISON IS FOUND OR ALL TABLES HAVE*/ 02537000
*   /* BEEN SEARCHED                                                 */ 02538000
*   /*                                                               */ 02539000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 02540000
*                                                                  0567 02541000
*   DO J=1 TO DIM(TABLEPTR);                                       0567 02542000
*                                                                  0567 02543000
         LA    J,1                                                 0567 02544000
@DL00567 DS    0H                                                  0568 02545000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02546000
*     /*                                                             */ 02547000
*     /* SET POINTER TO TABLE TO BE SEARCHED                         */ 02548000
*     /*                                                             */ 02549000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02550000
*                                                                  0568 02551000
*     TABADDR=TABLEPTR(J);                                         0568 02552000
         LR    @10,J                                               0568 02553000
         SLA   @10,2                                               0568 02554000
         L     TABADDR,TABLEPTR-4(@10)                             0568 02555000
*     PARMTYPE=J-2;                 /*                       @G55CP2P*/ 02556000
*                                                                  0569 02557000

         STH   @10,PARMTYPE                                        0569 02561000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02562000
*     /*                                                             */ 02563000
*     /* SEARCH TABLE UNTIL COMPARSION IS FOUND OR TABLE IS EXHAUSTED*/ 02564000
*     /*                                                             */ 02565000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02566000
*                                                                  0570 02567000
*     DO I=1 TO TABLENGH WHILE INPUTEXT(1:ELEMSIZE(I))¬=ELEMENT(I,1:    02568000
*           ELEMSIZE(I));                                          0570 02569000
         LA    I,1                                                 0570 02570000
         B     @DE00570                                            0570 02571000
@DL00570 L     @10,TEXTPTR-1                                       0570 02572000
         LR    @07,I                                               0570 02573000
         MH    @07,@CH02040                                        0570 02574000
         LR    @06,TABADDR                                         0570 02575000
         AL    @06,@CF02051                                        0570 02576000
         SLR   @05,@05                                             0570 02577000
         IC    @05,ELEMSIZE-3(@07,@06)                             0570 02578000
         BCTR  @05,0                                               0570 02579000
         ALR   @07,TABADDR                                         0570 02580000
         AL    @07,@CF02052                                        0570 02581000
         EX    @05,@SC02053                                        0570 02582000
         BE    @DC00570                                            0570 02583000
*     END;                          /* END OF SINGLE TABLE SEARCH  0571 02584000
*                                      LOOP                          */ 02585000
*                                                                  0571 02586000
         AL    I,@CF00050                                          0571 02587000
@DE00570 CH    I,TABLENGH(,TABADDR)                                0571 02588000
         BNH   @DL00570                                            0571 02589000
@DC00570 DS    0H                                                  0572 02590000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02591000
*     /*                                                             */ 02592000
*     /* IF I IS NOT GREATER THAN THE TABLE LENGTH A COMPARSION WAS  */ 02593000
*     /* FOUND. THE ADDRESS OF THE SWITCH TO BE SET WILL BE OBTAINED */ 02594000
*     /* AND THE LOOP WILL BE FORCED TO TERMINATE                    */ 02595000
*     /*                                                             */ 02596000
*     /***************************************************************/ 02597000
*                                                                  0572 02598000
*     IF I¬>TABLENGH THEN                                          0572 02599000
         CH    I,TABLENGH(,TABADDR)                                0572 02600000
         BH    @RF00572                                            0572 02601000
*       DO;                                                        0573 02602000
*         SWADDR=SWTCHPTR(J);                                      0574 02603000
         LR    @07,J                                               0574 02604000
         SLA   @07,2                                               0574 02605000
         L     SWADDR,SWTCHPTR-4(@07)                              0574 02606000
*         J=DIM(TABLEPTR)+1;                                       0575 02607000
*                                                                  0575 02608000
         LA    J,7                                                 0575 02609000
*         /***********************************************************/ 02610000
*         /*                                                         */ 02611000
*         /* IF THIS IS NOT A DUPLICATE VERB (INDICATED BY THE SWITCH*/ 02612000
*         /* BEING ZERO THEN THE SWITCH WILL BE SET TO THE POSITION  */ 02613000
*         /* OF THE ELEMENT IN THE TABLE THAT COMPARED TO THIS VERB  */ 02614000
*         /* AND THE VARIABLE 'TEXTPTR' WILL BE SET TO POINT PAST THE*/ 02615000
*         /* VERB JUST CHECKED.                                      */ 02616000
*         /*                                                         */ 02617000
*         /***********************************************************/ 02618000
*                                                                  0576 02619000
*         IF INPUTSW=0 THEN                                        0576 02620000
         CLI   INPUTSW(SWADDR),0                                   0576 02621000
         BNE   @RF00576                                            0576 02622000
*           DO;                                                    0577 02623000
*             INPUTSW=I;                                           0578 02624000
         STC   I,INPUTSW(,SWADDR)                                  0578 02625000
*             TEXTPTR=TEXTPTR+ELEMSIZE(I);                         0579 02626000
*                                                                  0579 02627000
         LR    @07,I                                               0579 02628000
         MH    @07,@CH02040                                        0579 02629000
         L     @06,TEXTPTR-1                                       0579 02630000
         LA    @06,0(,@06)                                         0579 02631000
         LR    @05,TABADDR                                         0579 02632000
         AL    @05,@CF02051                                        0579 02633000
         SLR   @04,@04                                             0579 02634000
         IC    @04,ELEMSIZE-3(@07,@05)                             0579 02635000
         ALR   @06,@04                                             0579 02636000
         STCM  @06,7,TEXTPTR                                       0579 02637000
*             /*******************************************************/ 02638000
*             /*                                                     */ 02639000
*             /* A TEST WILL NOW BE MADE TO DETERMINE IF THE VERB    */ 02640000
*             /* FOUND HAD A VARIABLE LENGTH FIELD. IF SO THE        */ 02641000
*             /* ELBAIRAV SUBROUTINE WILL BE CALLED TO PROCESS SAME. */ 02642000
*             /*                                                     */ 02643000
*             /*******************************************************/ 02644000
*                                                                  0580 02645000
*             IF VARYFLAG(I)=FOXFOX THEN                           0580 02646000
         ALR   @07,TABADDR                                         0580 02647000
         AL    @07,@CF02055                                        0580 02648000
         CLI   VARYFLAG-2(@07),X'FF'                               0580 02649000
         BNE   @RF00580                                            0580 02650000
*               DO;                                                0581 02651000
*                 CALL ELBAIRAV;                                   0582 02652000
*                                                                  0582 02653000
         BAL   @14,ELBAIRAV                                        0582 02654000
*                 /***************************************************/ 02655000
*                 /*                                                 */ 02656000
*                 /* DETERMINE IF VARIABLE FIELD WAS VALID. IF NOT   */ 02657000
*                 /* SET THE RETURN CODE TO 8.                       */ 02658000
*                 /*                                                 */ 02659000
*                 /***************************************************/ 02660000
*                                                                  0583 02661000
*                 IF RETCODE¬=0 THEN                               0583 02662000
         LH    @10,RETCODE                                         0583 02663000
         LTR   @10,@10                                             0583 02664000
         BZ    @RF00583                                            0583 02665000
*                   RETCODE=8;                                     0584 02666000
         MVC   RETCODE(2),@CH00048                                 0584 02667000
*                 ELSE                                             0585 02668000
*                   ;                                              0585 02669000
@RF00583 DS    0H                                                  0586 02670000
*               END;                                               0586 02671000
*                                                                  0586 02672000
*             /*******************************************************/ 02673000
*             /*                                                     */ 02674000
*             /* IF NO VARIABLE FIELD PRESENT SET RETURN CODE TO ZERO*/ 02675000
*             /* AND RETURN                                          */ 02676000
*             /*                                                     */ 02677000
*             /*******************************************************/ 02678000
*                                                                  0587 02679000
*             ELSE                                                 0587 02680000
*               RETCODE=0;                                         0587 02681000
         B     @RC00580                                            0587 02682000

*         /* CALLER                                                  */ 02691000

*/*    VALDEC - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D)    0602 02748000
*                                                                  0602 02749000
*      THIS SUBROUTINE WILL VALIDATE THE  VERB SUPPLIED BY THE     0602 02750000

*/*   VALCPU - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D)     0660 03055000
*                                                                  0660 03056000
*      THIS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED TO VERIFY THAT THE VARIABLE FIELD IN   03057000
*      THE CPU=X VERB SUPPLIED BY THE OPERATOR IN THE MODE COMMAND IS   03058000
*      VALID.  IF VALID THE VARIABLE FIELD IS CONVERTED TO BINARY.  IN  03059000
*      EITHER CASE A RETURN CODE IS SET AND CONTROL IS RETURNED TO THE  03060000
*      CALLER.  RETURN CODES ARE SET AS FOLLOWS:                   0660 03061000
*           0 - VALUE CONTAINED IN THE CPU=X VERB IS VALID         0660 03062000
*                AND HAS BEEN CONVERTED TO BINARY AND SAVED IN     0660 03063000
*                THE VARIABLE 'CPUID'                              0660 03064000
*            4 - THE CPU=X VERB CONTAINS MORE THAN FOUR OR LESS THAN    03065000
*                ONE CHARACTER OR ONE OR MORE OF THE CHARACTERS    0660 03066000
*                SPECIFIED IS NOT AN EBCDIC CHARACTER WITHIN THE   0660 03067000
*                OF 0 TO F.                                        0660 03068000
*            8 - THE CPU=X VERB CONTAINS THE ADDRESS OF A CPU NOT  0660 03069000
*                CURRENTLY ON LINE.                                0660 03070000
*                                                                  0660 03071000
*      THE EXTERNAL PROCEDURE CALLING THIS SUBROUTINE MUST:        0660 03072000
*         1. HAVE PROVIDED AN 18 WORD REGISTER SAVE AREA WHOSE ADDRESS  03073000
*            IS IN REGISTER 13 AT ENTRY TO THIS SUBROUTINE.        0660 03074000
*         2. HAVE SET THE VARIABLE 'TEXTPTR' TO POINT TO THE VARIABLE   03075000
*            TO BE CHECKED.                                        0660 03076000
*         3. HAVE PROVIDED AN 8 BYTE AREA KNOWN AS 'WORKAREA'.     0660 03077000
*         4. HAVE DECLARED THE VARIABLES KNOWN AS 'CPUID' AND      0660 03078000
*            'RETCODE'.                                            0660 03079000
*         5. HAVE A DSECT FOR CVT AND CSD.                         0660 03080000
*                                                                  0660 03081000
*                                                                  0660 03082000
*                                                                  0660 03083000
*                                                                    */ 03084000
*                                                                  0660 03085000
*VALCPU:                                                           0660 03086000
*   PROC;                                                          0660 03087000
*                                                                  0660 03088000
         B     @PB00011                                            0660 03089000
VALCPU   STM   @14,@12,@SA00011                                    0660 03090000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 03091000
*   /*                                                               */ 03092000
*   /* VALCPU INTERNAL DECLARES                                      */ 03093000
*   /*                                                               */ 03094000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 03095000
*                                                                  0661 03096000
*   DCL                                                            0661 03097000
*     CPUCHAR CHAR(4) BASED(TEXTPTR);/* CHARACTER(S) TO BE CHECKED BY   03098000
*                                      THIS SUBROUTINE               */ 03099000
*   DCL                                                            0662 03100000
*     WRKINDEX FIXED(31);           /* INDEX FOR WORKAREA            */ 03101000
*                                                                  0662 03102000

*   /*                                                               */ 03104000
*   /* VALCPU INTERNAL REGISTER DECLARES                             */ 03105000
*   /*                                                               */ 03106000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 03107000
*                                                                  0663 03108000

*     WKREG2 FIXED(31) REG(6) RESTRICTED;/* WORKREG FOR GENERATED SLL*/ 03110000

*   /*                                                               */ 03116000

*                                                                  0665 03120000
*   RETCODE=4;                                                     0665 03121000
*                                                                  0665 03122000
         MVC   RETCODE(2),@CH00038                                 0665 03123000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 03124000
*   /*                                                               */ 03125000
*   /* TEST TO DETERMINE IF NUMBER OF CHARACTERS PASSED IN THE CPU = */ 03126000
*   /* VERB IS BETWEEN 1 TO 4. IF SO CONTINUE TO PROCESS, IF NOT     */ 03127000
*   /* RETURN.                                                       */ 03128000
*   /*                                                               */ 03129000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 03130000
*                                                                  0666 03131000
*   IF CPIDLNGT>0&CPIDLNGT<5 THEN                                  0666 03132000

*     DO;                                                          0667 03137000
*                                                                  0667 03138000

*       /*                                                           */ 03140000
*       /* SET THE WORKAREA POINTER TO THE LAST BYTE IN THE WORKAREA */ 03141000
*       /* AND SET THE WORKAREA TO ZERO                              */ 03142000
*       /*                                                           */ 03143000
*       /*************************************************************/ 03144000
*                                                                  0668 03145000
*       WRKINDEX=LENGTH(WORKAREA);                                 0668 03146000

*       /*                                                           */ 03152000

*       /* AREA) AND EBCDIC CHARACTERS FROM A - F WILL BE CONVERTED  */ 03155000
*       /* TO HEX 'FA' - 'FF'.                                       */ 03156000
*       /*                                                           */ 03157000

*                                                                  0670 03159000

*         WORKAREA(WRKINDEX)=CPUCHAR(I);/* MOVE ONE CHARACTER TO   0671 03165000

*                                                                  0684 03250000

*   GEN(EJECT);                                                    0705 03332000

*                                                                  0706 03334000
*/*    WTO959I - SUBROUTINE OF MODE COMMAND PROCESSOR (IGF2603D)   0706 03335000
*                                                                  0706 03336000

*   /*****************************************************************/ 03362000
*   /*                                                               */ 03363000
*   /* DETERMINE IF INPUT RETCODE IS 4 OR 8. IF 4 OR 8 THEN CONTINUE,*/ 03364000

         MVC   BUF959(63),MSG959                                   0710 03390000

*       /*                                                           */ 03392000

*       /* MESSAGE WAS INITIALIZED WITH 'INVALID'                    */ 03394000

*       /*                                                           */ 03407000

*                                                                  0713 03411000
